    "id": "post-2025-01-30-7290814027138519040",
    "title": "This is an incredibly meaningful data point that dovetails with my ...",
    "date": "2025-01-30",
    "content": "This is an incredibly meaningful data point that dovetails with my growing hunch that AI necessarily transcends the two economic primitives we've inherited from the 20th century:\"\n\"\n1. the traditional corporation and\n\"\n2. the \"consumer economy.\n\"\nThe breakout AI product (which doesn't exist yet ‚Äî ChatGPT's release was nowhere close to what will be the \"iPhone moment\" for AI) will be neither for the enterprise* nor the consumer**; it will be for the 21st-century professional, the superempowered individual producer.\n\"\nOAI's Operator is likely a glimpse of what's coming: an integrated product that combines frontier capabilities with hooks into the public digital commons, iterative action, and permissioned access to your own salient/high-fidelity private data assets.\n\"\n*AI disintegrates traditional enterprises as roles are unbundled into reading, writing, and reasoning tasks during the adoption process and more effectively delegated to computers (see: Coase's theory of the firm, and consider that the very transaction costs that led to the emergence of massive bureaucracies to support customer creation at scale may be rapidly approaching zero) ‚Äî it's a social technology masquerading as just another information technology, and organizational transformation and reformation it ultimately necessitates is a lot more radical than anything seen in previous IT waves.\n\"\n\"**Advertising-driven media platforms (the first broad-based application of AI) formed the center of gravity of the internet economy over the last 20 years because of their tendencies toward ~natural monopoly and the latent attentional arbitrage opportunities in a consumer economy with reserve currency privilege; there's an alternative now, and it's what's making it possible to built new mega-tech companies that tax AI like a utility (or, possibly, capture value via masterful integration √† la Apple under Jobs and then Cook).",
