    "date": "2025-01-24",
    "content": "In the same way that I had a hunch two years ago that using ChatGPT (GPT-3 via the OpenAI API Playground) and then GPT-4 (available in March 2023) would be beneficial, I have a growing resonant hunch now that if you want to get ahead and stay ahead, you should practice delegating as much as you can to Operator (and whatever equivalent the other labs release). \"\n\"\nUnderstanding the ways it works, the ways it doesn't, and the surprising minutia required to make it work (like setting up new email accounts, etc.) will give you a massive, massive edge.\n\"\nAnother AI paradox: the tech wipes out middle management; everyone is a middle manager now.\n\"\n\"Time start exercising those managerial skillsets (or cultivate them if you've only ever been an IC)!",
