    "id": "post-2025-01-22-7287859751932055554",
    "title": "If you're ever feeling overwhelmed with commitments, obligations, s...",
    "date": "2025-01-22",
    "content": "If you're ever feeling overwhelmed with commitments, obligations, seemingly disjointed goals and responsibilities, constrained resources, and are operating in a highly volatile context, I cannot recommend highly enough going for a 60 to 90-minute walk \"with\" ChatGPT Pro (or Claude).\"\n\"\nWhile walking, literally verbally articulate the long-form stream of consciousness flowing your head until you've nothing more to say, sending your thoughts through your AirPods and into a voice memo app that has automatic transcription ‚Äî all this in response to the simple question, \"What's going on?\" \n\"\nOnce you have your thoughts recorded, copy and paste the transcription into (and this is my recommended model as of January 2025) o1 Pro. Wait a few minutes, and then read its response very carefully (or play it back via computer-generated audio! I'm a fan of the Sol and Arbor voices, personally), and then work with it, probably in only one or two more turns, to figure out exactly what you should do next. \n\"\n(Determine exactly how much time you have to take that unexpected next step‚Äîwhether it's a minute, an hour, or maybe more‚Äîand then make sure that you're totally sold on the right recommendation.)\n\"\nBeing able to bring order to chaos on your own time with an infinitely patient thought partner, that (who?) costs $200 a month, is a monumental achievement in technology.\n\"\n\"PS - in light my ambitious growth goals for 2025 and disciplined approach to bootstrapping both my services and product business, \"we\" arrived at one simple thing I can get done this morning, I wouldn't have otherwise: record, redact, and post a recording of me using Powerline soup-to-nuts as soon as I open up my daily voice memo to demonstrate how it actually works in practice...video and post coming soon!",
