    "id": "post-2025-01-17-7286065218047098880",
    "title": "After a great chat with Mark Amtower, I‚Äôve started to get a bit mor...",
    "date": "2025-01-17",
    "content": "After a great chat with Mark Amtower, I‚Äôve started to get a bit more clarity on what could be coming with the next leap in AI‚Äîparticularly the rise of ‚Äúagentic‚Äù systems.\"\n\"\nAgent\" is one of those buzzwords that's been getting lots of lip service, but few results; however, recent signals from leading AI labs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc.) suggest it‚Äôs closer than even skeptics like me had thought.\n\"\nInstead of us doing all the data wrangling and action-taking, these more advanced AI systems will be able to reason through complex decisions, take multiple steps on their own via \"tools\" (like browsing the web or sending emails), and even coordinate with other agents to accomplish a goal.\n\"\nThis new wave of AI also has a direct impact on how we work and manage teams‚Äîcue the¬†\"middle management paradox\n\"\nOn one hand, these agentic systems will handle some meaningful scope of routine decisions and communication tasks, meaning traditional ‚Äúmiddle manager‚Äù roles are not unlikely to shrink in number, but also expand tremendously managers' scope of responsibility.\n\"\nThis means the skills that good middle managers have‚Äîcoordinating across teams and silos, spotting and preventing issues early, ensuring smooth collaboration and implementing QA gates‚Äîwill become¬†incredibly valuable. Think of it as ‚Äúmanaging AI employees‚Äù: you‚Äôll need people who can oversee, guide, and quality-check the new fleet of AI agents so they produce the right outcomes (rather than wandering off to do who-knows-what with your time and budget!).\n\"\nA few things I‚Äôm keeping top-of-mind:\n\"\n1.\tNetworking & Discovery Tools \n\"\nAdvanced research tools like¬†Happenstance and proto-agentic products like Gemini Deep Research¬†are raising the bar for how quickly we can connect with the¬†right¬†people. As our networks become even more connected via AI-driven research and facilitation of high-quality introductions, the accelerated growth playbooks that prioritize quality over quantity become more feasible.\n\"\n2.\tData Sharing & Redaction \n\"\nAs AI tools get more capable, they‚Äôll see more of our sensitive information. We have to be strategic about what data we feed them (prompt injection and jailbreaking are both salient challenges, especially), and build workflows that protect any proprietary content or personal info.\n\"\n3. Preparing for Agentic AI\n\"\nThe real shift will come when AI moves from a ‚Äúsuggestion engine‚Äù to an actual agent‚Äînot only responsively, but even proactively handling multi-step tasks, booking travel, following up with leads, and even deciding when to escalate issues to humans.\n\"\nCurious to hear if others are prepping for agentic AI...\n\"\n\"What are you doing to integrate new tools or future-proof your teams?",
