    "id": "post-2025-01-06-7282073777335681024",
    "title": "The job loss discourse around AI drives me nuts",
    "date": "2025-01-06",
    "content": "The job loss discourse around AI drives me nuts.\"\n\"\nNo \"one\" is getting replaced.\n\"\nRoles (jobs) are bundles of tasks. In light of computers that can read, write, and reason, it should be self-evident that these roles will necessarily be unbundled, and the tasks of which they are comprised delegated accordingly, many to machines that can now handle them. The overall process is then decomposed into new bundles that may, at first, seem rather alien.\n\"\nYes, this way of working looks different than what we've gotten used to in the 20th century. Yes, this presents challenges, especially for people who derive a lot of self-worth from their ability to primarily do something a certain way, with the outcome being secondary. \n\"\nJust embrace it. Everyone has access to the technology.\n\"\nWith the release of the reasoning models, it's not that there might be wage deflation in traditional white-collar roles. There already is deflation, just not widely diffused. The rate at which this happens is largely a consequence of macroeconomic factors and policy issues outside the scope of this post. However, this overall trajectory is significantly less uncertain than it was even a year ago.\n\"\nIf you thought that by getting on a particular career track, you would be guaranteed some sort of income by doing things in a certain way, then I'm sorry. The reality is quite different, and with happiness being something like reality minus expectations, this will be the source of some tribulation.\n\"\nHowever, what I can guarantee you is that on the other side of a radical retooling effort, your real wages, degrees of freedom, and overall energy levels will be significantly higher. But this all starts with the realization that you don't deserve a single thing, especially in a relatively free global market.\n\"\nTo make meaningful progress, you must anchor your \"objective function\" to some other person's satisfaction that a real problem they have‚Äîa barrier in the way of attaining their own good goals‚Äîhas been satisfactorily removed by you through a combination of technology and action. Get the reps in, and you will generate new expertise that will allow you to differentiate yourself, which is the source of wage appreciation and profit.\n\"\n\"Fate leads the willing and drags the unwilling. Today would be a good day to get started on the path into the 21st century.",
