    "content": "It's been almost a month since I shelled out $200 for the new, higher ChatGPT tier.\"\n\"\nWith frequent, daily use, it's clear: o1 Pro is overpowered; it's smarter than I am. \n\"\nI used to be able to get away with skimming SOTA model responses and muddling through to the next task.\n\"\nNow, I have to read the responses carefully, chew on the content, consider that it might have come to better conclusions in areas I'd considered myself an expert.\n\"\nThe prose is dense. It's thoughtful. I sense that it's telling me things that are true that I may not want to hear‚Äîsometime obliquely, as if it anticipates some defensiveness.\n\"\nThe bottleneck is my own context window, then: the rate at which I can take the right action to generate more data to pop back into the exchange (thoughts via dictation, console output while testing code changes, the transcript of a voice assistant conversation with a third-party from whom I need more information).\n\"\nMeans that knowing where to point the coin-operated computer will be of greater importance‚Äîgood goals, ordered desire, \"taste.\n\"\n\"I'm seeing sparks of ASI.",
