    "id": "post-2024-12-29-7279148013799763969",
    "title": "If test time compute turns out to be unreasonably effective for cer...",
    "date": "2024-12-29",
    "content": "If test time compute turns out to be unreasonably effective for certain problems, and I imagine it will, it fundamentally alters the translation function of money. \"\n\"\nThis has significant implications for how we think about capital allocation as a skill in general. \n\"\nVenture capitalists, startup founders, and states have been relatively constrained in how they can deploy their capital due to transaction costs and scarce talent. \n\"\nAs a result, they spend a huge amount of money on \"search\" by developing brands and operating large bureaucratic administrative functions to attract and select applicants. \n\"\nThey also horizontally scale the specialized labor necessary to accelerate core product development and growth, using emergent social technologies like scrum, the formalization of tracked careers, and the software that acts as glue for this larger form.\n\"\nInstead of cutting checks to small teams, one might very precisely point a swarm of AI system components toward a fertile problem space and put coins in the test time compute machine.\n\"\nThis could allow you to get to the heart of a particular problem and discover new profit-generating secrets in a way that bypasses the traditional bottlenecks. (These bottlenecks led us to develop the various corporate forms, good & best management practices, etc. that we now largely take for granted ‚Äî some of these will prove durable; most of what's been published in the \"business books\" section will not.)\n\"\nI increasingly advocate for radical reform (~50% of my income comes from implementation, so we're beyond the speculation phase), not just of existing institutions in light of AI, but more importantly in how financiers, entrepreneurs, and lawmakers with an eye toward the frontier pursue their projects and implement infrastructure for durable growth. \n\"\nWhen you consider allocating your attention or resources to something you believe will move things forward, pause and consider if there might be AI-powered components that can accelerate your progress tenfold. \n\"\nThis consideration has transformed my participation in the economy and helped me overcome the limiting factors and beliefs of the 20th century, allowing me to create new roles and adopt the skill sets and mindset needed to thrive in the 21st century.\n\"\nWhat will this mean for you?\n\"\n\"IDK ‚Äî but things that were impossible are now possible; go forth and find out!",
