    "id": "post-2024-12-15-7273859589178068992",
    "title": "If there's one thing you commit to in 2025, it's this:\"\n\"\"\n\"Build a...",
    "date": "2024-12-15",
    "content": "If there's one thing you commit to in 2025, it's this:\"\n\"\nBuild a piece of software that someone uses. \n\"\nThat makes their life better in some small but meaningful way. \n\"\nAnd build it by yourself.\n\"\nYou can do it‚Äîand you should, ESPECIALLY if you've never done it before.\n\"\nYou don't need an engineering team. You don't need equity financing. You don't need a business plan. You don't need a whiteboard. You don't need wireframes. You don't need mockups. You don't need scrum. You don't need JIRA. You don't need GitHub. You don't need a course. You don't need Cursor.\n\"\nYou need $20 for a month of ChatGPT Plus, a single person for whom you commit to building something they want/need/love, a few hours of focused concentration, and a commitment to finishing what you start.\n\"\nThat's literally it.\n\"\nDo this once, get validation by an impartial third party per their recurring use, and you will never go back.\n\"\nSoftware is an incredible technology that lets you turn thoughts into a capital asset, and thanks to these new models, if you have the right goal, ask the right questions, and relentlessly pursue the satisfaction of the person for whom you're building the thing, you can create something that gives you leverage, basically ex nihilo.\n\"\n\"Now, go get to it!",
