    "id": "post-2024-12-13-7273362691082145794",
    "title": "The single biggest barrier to getting a huge amount of value out of...",
    "date": "2024-12-13",
    "content": "The single biggest barrier to getting a huge amount of value out of advanced AI models, especially with tools like o1 Pro while coding, is that you need to make liberal use of the dictation feature. \"\n\"\nThankfully, this feature is now built into the native applications for both iOS and Mac. \n\"\nIf you are still typing, you're doing it wrong.\n\"\nIn practice, when I have a task or feature I want the system to help with, I click on the microphone icon, pace around my office, and speak‚Äîsometimes one word at a time, very slowly, and sometimes very quickly: I work through my own \"chains of thought\" to make sense of what I want and provide enough context until I'm satisfied I've said everything necessary.\n\"\nThose 2, 10, or even 20 minutes up front, during which you get all those salient thoughts out of your head and into the state-of-the-art model, will save you hours or even days. \n\"\nThis, of course, should be coupled with as much high fidelity, rich context as you can pull from elsewhere, especially including full meeting transcripts and entire code bases.\n\"\nIn short: Stop typing; start talking. \n\"\nKeep going until you've achieved crystal clarity on your intention and provided sufficient information, even if somewhat brief, to o1 Pro or Sonnet. \n\"\n\"It's a meaningful change in habit and somewhat awkward initially, but it is a necessary step toward truly going AI native.",
