    "title": "for the stuff you can't delegate to AI, use Upwork:\"\n\"\"\n\"1",
    "date": "2024-11-20",
    "content": "for the stuff you can't delegate to AI, use Upwork:\"\n\"\n1. record a Loom video (ramble for as long as you'd like), explaining in general what you need, acceptance criteria, etc. (I just did this for a video editing job w/ specifics around redaction)\n\"\n2. pipe the transcript through o1-preview (accessible via paid Chat accounts or the OAI dev portal) and ask it to create a bespoke Upwork RFP, including pricing & packaging\n\"\n3. post\n\"\n4. copy and paste every proposal back into the o1-preview chat and ask it to pick the best person for the job\n\"\n5. back to work\n\"\nAI is super helpful both for compression (this has been the case for a while) and reasoning (crafting the terms of the contract, then selecting the best candidate!, via o1).\n\"\n\"I've done this a bunch of times now and have only had good experiences, w/ almost zero management overhead.",
