    "id": "post-2024-11-15-7263178533429039104",
    "title": "√Ä la Buffet's \"be fearful when others are greedy and to be greedy o...",
    "date": "2024-11-15",
    "content": "√Ä la Buffet's \"be fearful when others are greedy and to be greedy only when others are fearful,\" I'd recommend betting on rapid AI acceleration as the \"hitting a wall\" meme makes its way through mainstream media.\"\n\"\nTake a complex, proprietary dataset:\n\"\n- a codebase,\n- an M&A deal draft,\n- a series of meeting transcripts with sharp experts, etc.\n\"\nAnd ask o1-preview (via Chat or the OpenAI developer portal) to tell you \"one thing it knows to be true that few of the individuals who contributed to the creation of said content would agree with agree with it on + what you should do about it in 60s or less.\n\"\nA \"stochastic parrot\" (or even an impressive summarizer, eg last-gen models like 3 Opus) wouldn't be able produce the output you'll see...\n\"\nIn 2024, the question for executives and operators curious about AI was, \"what would you do if you had a naive but well-read and eager-to-please analyst at your beck and call?\n\"\nIn 2025, that question will be, \"what would you do if you had army of low-cost PHDs you could spin up like EC2 instances and point at your data lake?\n\"\nWe're officially past the \"computers that can handle reading/writing/rote information translation and administrative trivia phase\"; what comes next will be more interesting ‚Äî and more destabilizing for your existing organizational structure if you don't get ahead of it, and that starts with getting first-hand experience.\n\"\n\"No courses. No second-hand advisory from SMEs. Just a focused hour or two, pushing this new class of models to tackle tasks that were literally impossible for computers to handle a few months ago, therefore developing an intuition about where you can and should lead your organization out on this new \"simulated reasoning\" frontier that's just opening up.",
