    "id": "post-2024-11-04-7259280651873390592",
    "title": "If OpenAI secures a durable lead in long-running \"reasoning\" capabi...",
    "date": "2024-11-04",
    "content": "If OpenAI secures a durable lead in long-running \"reasoning\" capabilities (they have, and by a lot, with o1 as of now) on one end of the latency spectrum and the best real-time voice in the other, they will have executed a brilliant pincer movement that leaves little room for other labs: Opus 3 definitely still has an edge when it comes to writing per se, and the NotebookLM podcast duo is excellent as well; but, these are still both slices of the AI value chain that will be squeezed at both ends as end users will come to value responsive interaction and output quality, with all else being relatively less important.\"\n\"\nPractically, if you want to catch a glimpse of what's coming, tinker with the o1-preview model via Chat by giving it your hardest problems (with as much context as possible!) and going for a walk-and-talk with 4o advanced voice mode (also available via chat).\n\"\n\"It's at the touchpoints between these simulated \"system 2\" and \"1\" capabilities, respectively, that we'll see some of the most interesting applied AI innovations in 2025 (and it's a qualitatively different experience that what we've become used to, even in just 2 years, with text-based, fast chat interfaces).",
