    "id": "post-2024-10-25-7255692360439746560",
    "title": "Quantity in Private; Quality in Public: Using AI to Challenge Yours...",
    "date": "2024-10-25",
    "content": "Quantity in Private; Quality in Public: Using AI to Challenge Yourself to Excel Profesionally\"\n\"\nMany companies are eager to leverage AI to gain a competitive edge. \n\"\nBut the real opportunity isn't in simply automating tasks to increase output. \n\"\nThe magic happens when you use AI to elevate the quality of your work.\n\"\nHow? \n\"\nLet AI push you in new directions. Have it challenge your assumptions and spark ideas you hadn't considered:\n\"\n- simulate prospect objections\n- \"steelman\" counteraguments\n- enumerate three \"highly precise, hard-hitting follow-up questions that reference the source where appropriate and, if sufficiently addressed, would be likely elicit novel and actionable insights that would catch the attention of [target audience]\" (one of my personal favorite prompts)\n\"\nEmbrace the cognitive discomfort, like pushing for a new PR in the gym. \n\"\nAI may reduce mundane tasks, but it makes work more demanding in the best way - by compelling you to be more excellent, which comes as a function of rapid iteration as you push AI to push you to elevate the quality of your ideas and work product.\n\"\nWhere to begin? \n\"\nFirst, give employees access to general AI tools. Then bring in an expert to help early adopters delegate reading/writing tasks to AI more effectively. Encourage them to share learnings publicly.\n\"\nThe key is trusting the process. Let people experiment, find what energizes them, and stay customer-obsessed. The collective lessons will organically reveal AI's potential for your business.\n\"\nAs internal know-how grows, start encoding insights into new processes and structures. Let AI guide you in setting significantly more ambitious goals as what you can precisely do that was previously impossible becomes clear.\n\"\nThe companies (and leaders) that will thrive with AI aren't rushing to automate everything. They're empowering their people to harness this incredible technology to push the boundaries of what they can achieve.\n\"\nHow will you challenge yourself and your team to excel with AI?\n\"\n\"H/t Mark Amtower",
