    "id": "post-2024-10-25-7255566570091941888",
    "title": "How can AI help organizations identify the real vs",
    "date": "2024-10-25",
    "content": "How can AI help organizations identify the real vs. perceived flows of information, value, and money? \"\n\"\nAre there ways to use word-crunching computers to identify gaps between the formal and real shapes of a business, ripe opportunities for BPR-style AI integration initiatives?\n\"\nIn recent discussions with other applied AI professionals, I've been exploring this intersection between quantitative data and qualitative insights, particularly through generative AI's ability to help analyze emotional states and energy levels derived from transcripts of discovery interviews.  \n\"\nFor example, I had an interesting experience with a staffing and recruiting company‚Äîwhile mapping processes, we quantified how much time each task took, but, we also asked which tasks were energy draining versus energy giving for the frontline operators. \n\"\nThis approach highlighted where AI automation could be beneficial in terms of reducing cycle times and boosting efficiency while ALSO ensuring human operators focus on the tasks that truly drive engagement and value ‚Äî contra (or maybe a corollary to?) pure Taylorism!\n\"\nThis synergy between human expertise and AI scaffolding can create a dynamic and innovative approach to business process reengineering. It's not just about reducing cycle times; it‚Äôs critical to maintain vibrant energy levels in teams to drive success and drive forward progress via innovation vs. latent customer needs.\n\"\nThat new surplus energy and attention can be reinvested in \"micro-R&D/BD,\" and that's where the long-term gains from unexpected asymmetric upside opportunities come from.\n\"\nI'd love to hear your thoughts on this, Fernando Barroso Gallegos (and h/t for an engaging chat yesterday that spurred this post)! What do you think about leveraging AI in this way? \n\"\n\"#AI #BusinessProcessReengineering #Collaboration #Innovation",
    "excerpt": "How can AI help organizations identify the real vs. perceived flows of information, value, and money? \" \"\" \"Are there ways to use word-crunching computers to...",
    "type": "post",
