    "id": "post-2024-09-23-7243966992624361472",
    "title": "Lot of hype at the moment about \"non-technical\" people building sof...",
    "date": "2024-09-23",
    "content": "Lot of hype at the moment about \"non-technical\" people building software with AI-powered tools like Claude Pro and Cursor and Replit.\"\n\"\nAnd it's totally warranted!\n\"\nBUT, there are two things you can't download that are absolutely necessary for you, someone who did not study computer science in undergrad, to get that first magical rep in where you go from idea to web application that you can send to anyone to use:\n\"\n1. At least 4 deep work cycles (~8 hours total): in practice, if you're able to truly put the blinders on for 1‚Äì2 work days and only focus on going 0 to 1 with your first web application (that works!), you can absolutely get there. \n\"\nPreviously (and I'm speaking personally here), this step took weeks, much of which was spent scouring StackOverflow, which is enough friction to dissuade a lot of creative word-people like myself to not take something to production.\n\"\n2. Desire: This is generally important for any difficult work endeavor; but, when it comes to this particular task, it's critical. The good news is once you get that first burst of energy from seeing your code work and you get an outcome that would have been impossible or taken you weeks of manual work, you'll never go back. It's quite a high. \n\"\nBut, before and after that point, there will be many bits of confusion and frustration you'll need to endure‚Äîand they're a lot easier to get through if you have both a carrot and stick established at the beginning. \n\"\nI'd recommend doing the follow to kick this off right: do a 30‚Äì60-minute remote interview with a colleague about their most annoying workflow problems (e.g., drafting follow-up emails or post-call CRM entries) with an AI notetaker like Fireflies.ai in attendance. \n\"\nThen, pipe that transcript into Claude Pro and ask it to help you ideate on, spec out, and then implement in code a little app that would solve your colleague's problem.\n\"\nCommit to delivery of a URL that they can visit on their own time where they'll get access to something that will make their life easier per one of the problems latent in the transcript‚Äîset an immutable due date!\n\"\nOnce you have a due date (stick) and clear good (carrot), you'll be in good shape.\n\"\nFrom that point it's a matter of grit, a balance of furious forward movement as you make quick changes and test on your local machine and deep thought as you grok the AI's explanation of what it's doing/how it all works together (don't gloss over these parts, and ask questions if you're confused!), and unbroken attention.\n\"\nBonus: if you want to go even faster, use superwhisper to talk (in lieu of typing) to Claude (or ChatGPT) as you work with it.\n\"\n\"Good luck!",
