    "title": "AI as information technology is less interesting than the social te...",
    "date": "2024-09-07",
    "content": "AI as information technology is less interesting than the social technologies it unlocks ‚Äî more important that what AI is or does is what it means for how work get done by human teams.\"\n\"\nThat's why I've been spending a lot of time crafting the GSD Triple-A (Accelerated AI Adoption) playbook.\n\"\nA preview of the first section:\n\"\nThis starts with arming all frontline employees (sales, service, support) with general purpose tooling, e.g., Claude enterprise + a meeting notetaker like Fireflies.ai; customer interactions can also be mediated by a product piloted by a small cross-functional team, although it'll produce lower-fidelity data generally since software interactions are more constrained.\n\"\nReward employees who frontload and backload customer interactions with coaching the SOTA Claude model, informed by whatever salient data you have by the party (including that most recent transcript) and a bit of intent. You can do this by setting a measurable team-wide target of \"meeting recordings shared in Slack channel x with actionable insights generated during a debrief\" to make these units of work legible; after a month or so, with some artful weekly managerial intervention + attention paid to actual v. target, this AI-enhanced loop will become a cultural habit.\n\"\nExecutives should use AI-as-telescope/miscroscope to mine left- and right-tailed exceptions from all recordings at a regular cadence and:\n\"\n1. Directly reward the creators of right-tailed customer experiences,\n\"\n2. Do RCAs on left-tailed outcomes and delegate intervention responsibilities to the appropriate level of management (could be direct, but doesn't have to be), and\n\"\n3. Incorporate those data into weekly sense-making + accountable action planning syncs (the only live team meeting you need in a truly AI-native, remote, async organization) and use them to reduce uncertainty around longer-term goals (3x in parallel at 50% certainty targets at the beginning of a trimester [and high WoW volatility] is good for \"order out of chaos\" initiatives; you can follow a similar pattern to \"fight entropy\"/boost reliability with 1 target over the same period, but starting at an 85% conf. level).\n\"\nThe key is creating the right AI-powered virtuous cycle at the point of contact between the org and the external world, where value is created/exchanged, and then, as a function of having to make those interactions legible to AI for it to be valuable, cultivating a data asset that can be queried directly by as many other people at the company as possible; the bottoms-up legibility is complemented by top-down legibility (executive meetings where the most complex problems are surfaced are also published to Slack), enabling both democratic participation in the pursuit of the unifying objective, while enabling the entire organization to take aligned action via centralized intention-setting.\n\"\nThe real twist? \n\"\n\"Given this setup, the same person can step into frontline and executive roles in the same day...",
