    "id": "post-2024-08-30-7235274493785485314",
    "title": "A startup called Magic recently announced that trained a 100 millio...",
    "date": "2024-08-30",
    "content": "A startup called Magic recently announced that trained a 100 million token context window model.\"\n\"\nFor most commentators the headline on this is \"agents are now more feasible.\" I remain an agent skeptic.\n\"\nWhat's more interesting, though, is what this means for managers: if, say, you were able to digitize EVERYTHING a department of ~100 employees saw, said, or heard during a given workweek, literally all of that data could fit into a single prompt, meaning you, as an executive or department head leading a team of that size, could rely on straight interpretation of the timestamped facts delivered by a highly intelligent and dispassionate third-party.\n\"\nWhat would this mean for your standard weekly sync meeting?\n\"\n\"Worth thinking about the practical implications as \"record-by-default\" + Slack as system-of-record become the norm for remote, asynchronous, and fractional 21st-century organizations...",
