    "title": "AI products probably worth building:\"\n\"\"\n\"- pipeline that reliably ...",
    "date": "2024-08-22",
    "content": "AI products probably worth building:\"\n\"\n- pipeline that reliably redacts sensitive information from raw multimedia eg Loom videos, Fireflies A/V (publish more compelling long-form content, more often; everyone gets a \"reality show\" that can be mediated by AI for the good stuff w/o someone having to actually consume the whole thing, but no third-party's secrets are shared)\n\"\n- enterprise reporting on all the data submitted to the organization's LLM web app that somehow also preserves individual privacy (c-suite understands what people are using it for + what's actually happening in the org's \"unconscious mind,\" latent in the data, while also mitigating the chilling effect of users worrying about the legibility of their particular conversations)\n\"\n- a sort of e2e integrated communication tool that allows you to record a Loom video, send it to someone, have it frontloaded with an extremely compressed and high-quality representation of the content (I do this manually by piping the content into 3 Opus before sending an email with the video link in the PS), and then allowing the user to jump into a conversation with a voice agent who continues the thread on your behalf and is pre-loaded with all relevant context in its system prompt, the transcript of which is shared with the sender in both compressed and raw form; I do this now manually by stringing together Loom, VAPI, and Claude (true async, remote, discursive, personalized communication)\n\"\nAll of these things are sort of possible now but prohibitively expensive (measured in no. of clicks) to do as frequently as I'd like.\n\"\n\"Comment or DM if any of these resonate w you...",
