    "content": "Have a growing hunch that knowledge work will be less and less \"business-as-usual\" (computers can increasingly take that on) and more \"hackathon-style sprints with diverse, cross-functional teams of a-players.\"\n\"\nGiven that work can be done increasingly:\n\"\n- remotely,\n- asynchronously,\n- fractionally (ad hoc spinning up experts like EC2 instances vs. FTEs), and\n- globally (the talent pool gets way more liquid as cultural and linguistic barriers continue to fall, esp. due to AI but also gen Z workers coming online),\n\"\nthis seems inevitable to me (and I'm starting to see the beginnings of this kind of thing already).\n\"\n\"Individuals and organizations would be wise to get ahead of this shift sooner rather than later.",
