    "date": "2024-08-17",
    "content": "Definitely seeing a new AI-native role emerge: someone curious and good at asking questions of top-1% experts within an org to unstick the tacit knowledge in their heads and then encode it into eg a Claude project, custom GPT, application system prompt and scale access.\"\n\"\nIf you're not doing this now, you should.\n\"\n1. Get ChaGPT Enterprise / Team or Claude Team accounts for some or all of your employees,\n\"\n2. Hire an insatiably curious gen-Z'er with high verbal intelligence,\n\"\n3. Give him or her a company Otter.ai license,\n\"\n4. Negotiate a 30-day goal of 25 interviews recorded & 5 custom GPTs (or Claude projects) derived from those transcripts used daily by other employees (each should have >=1 DAU).\n\"\n5. Have them present their findings and a repository with all the primary source data at a recorded/optional 60m presentation that includes their methodology, findings, outcomes, surprises, next steps, and Q&A.\n\"\nVoila! \n\"\n\"In just under a month, you're well on your way to cultivating a meaningful data asset and transforming your organization with AI.",
