    "date": "2024-08-11",
    "content": "Excellent case study from a Google Deepmind researcher about how AI enables real productivity boosts in his own work.\"\n\"\nLess \"delegate project to long-running agent\" and more \"continuous delegation and orchestration of little slices of your workflow.\n\"\nThese add up ‚Äî and compound, as you start getting things done significantly faster (vs. horizontally scaled throughput per se).\n\"\nThis reflects what I've experienced (and seen with clients) ‚Äî the gains from AI require constant experimentation, agility, managerial skills; and, ultimately, you to completely reconfigure your working relationship with your personal computer + leaders to rearchitect the way work gets done by teams.\n\"\n\"If you're serious about AI & digital transformation, understand that anything short of a radical reconfiguration will only yield marginal benefits...the good news is, innovators on your team can take right-sized steps toward figuring out how that could and should look.",
