    "id": "post-2024-08-05-7226253237002080257",
    "title": "This-gen AI is most useful as a COMPRESSOR, not a GENERATOR",
    "date": "2024-08-05",
    "content": "This-gen AI is most useful as a COMPRESSOR, not a GENERATOR.\"\n\"\nYou need to first acquire high-quality, salient, rich, proprietary data to make it useful‚Äîand then work with the systems to figure out how to make good decisions (eg by using Claude to augment your own hypothesis generation) that, in turn, help you acquire more...\n\"\nGood use rewards originality, risk-taking, and novelty; if what you end up with is more of the same (the buzzy term for this is \"slop\"), then you're doing it wrong.\n\"\n1. Help people solve difficult problems. \n\"\n2. Record the process. \n\"\n3. Use those recordings as input to AI make sense of what you learn, share insights, and accelerate progress with snappier follow-up communication and action, teaching others how to do what you've figured out, and/or building bits and pieces of software.\n\"\n\"More is more. Now, go get the good stuff!",
