    "date": "2024-08-02",
    "content": "Ever wish you had your own high-tech personal assistant like Moneypenny from James Bond?\"\n\"\nNow, with AI tools like Vapi, Replit, Anthropic's Claude, superwhisper, and ElevenLabs, you can ... here's how:\n\"\nhttps://lnkd.in/eMvSChcX\n\"\n\"[meta-comment for my fellow entrepreneurs & indie consultants out there ‚Äî¬†I recorded this whole thing on a whim via Loom a few months back, used it as a lead magnet by putting the original raw video behind an email capture form, then posted a micro-RFP in the Descript Discord server for an editor to create something that would be a bit more of a fit for YouTube w/ an opening teaser etc., immediately had ~5 people reach out to me, shelled out a very small amount of money, and within a couple of days, had the final edit delivered directly to me w/ basically 0 management overhead ... that is the \"future of work\" IMO, and the key is knowing what to delegate (I have neither the time nor desire to DIY) + how (use AI assistance to take the raw material + your dictated intent and re-package it into right-sized specs to attract proposals, all of which you can run through AI to surface the good ones for manual review) + \"where\" (private communities where experts convene, often around a particular software product that pro's use, or general platforms like Upwork); things get really interesting when you get creative with comp.: I try to aim for some up-front, some upon delivery, and a bonus payment upon achieving a particular result that's out of both my and the contractor's immediate control, e.g., no. of views of content, revenue generated from a particular marketing funnel.]",
