    "date": "2024-08-01",
    "content": "If you're an indie consultant, what CRM (or system of record) do you use, if any?\"\n\"\nI've tried to use Hubspot and SFDC (mostly to develop empathy for clients who've implemented them at larger scale) and am frankly pretty shocked by how clunky and cumbersome the UX is (esp. workflow integration ‚Äî¬†really slows me down...)\n\"\nMy current \"system-of-record\" is some combination of my business checking account, Stripe and Square data, my Fireflies / Otter recordings, Figma Figjam board (I usually spin one up per client and keep all of our working material in there), and Google contacts (and LinkedIn, of course)...\n\"\nI've tried Clay dot earth (I like the simplicity of the app + daily reminders to consider connecting with folks I haven't touched base with in a while) but ended up moving away from that, too.\n\"\n\"Curious if anyone w/ a 1‚Äì5-person business has a core data system they like and rely on?",
