    "content": "2004: you ask search engines questions...\"\n\"\n2024: search engines ask YOU questions!\n\"\nThis might be AI's most important feature. \n\"\nGood questions invite focus and ultimately action. \n\"\nSo, if these systems are good enough compressors, then with enough context data - with enough high fidelity proprietary data in their context window that's salient to your life and your goals, along with the breadth of its pre-training set and whatever other sources it's able to semi-automatically retrieve from...\n\"\nThen, given some specified higher-order goal, it should be able to prompt you into thinking about things in the right way and then taking the right action.\n\"\nThe search engine that asks you questions.\n\"\nThe LLM that prompts you.\n\"\n\"The curious AI that uses motivational interviewing to help you accelerate in the right direction!",
