    "title": "As a follow-up to my recent interview with strategy expert Daniel M...",
    "date": "2024-07-19",
    "content": "As a follow-up to my recent interview with strategy expert Daniel Montgomery, here's a little more about what we talked about:\"\n\"\nAI enables \"information liquidity\" - the ability to quickly gather, analyze and make sense of vast amounts of complex qualitative data that was previously inaccessible. \n\"\nThis gives leaders unprecedented strategic sensitivity.\n\"\nRather than replacing human judgment, AI enhances it by filtering out the noise and surfacing the most salient insights for discussion. \n\"\nThe less you use AI directly in strategy meetings, the more effective those meetings become.\n\"\nAI doesn't just help you move faster - it enables you to confidently move in entirely new directions. \n\"\nBy efficiently testing ideas and gathering feedback, AI empowers companies to explore uncharted strategic territory.\n\"\nTo leverage AI for strategy, focus on two things: \n\"\n1) Delegating information gathering/processing to AI, freeing up human attention for sensemaking. \n\"\n2) Using AI to rapidly acquire new capabilities and deliver innovative strategic experiments.\n\"\nThe future of strategy is human and machine intelligence working in concert, not competition. \n\"\nOrganizations that embrace this paradigm will navigate uncertainty with unrivaled agility.\n\"\nCheck out the full podcast discussion here: https://lnkd.in/eY_AUUuH\n\"\n\"(Stay tuned for more ...)",
