    "id": "post-2024-06-19-7209245513416617984",
    "title": "If you really want takeaways from a key meeting to stick, AI genera...",
    "date": "2024-06-19",
    "content": "If you really want takeaways from a key meeting to stick, AI generated minutes that you can review and meditate on are a great start. \"\n\"\nBut to take things to the next level, you can turn that information into a catchy via tools like Suno. I've started doing this on a regular basis, including after my own weekly OKR sync, which I conduct solo except for the assistance of AI systems like Claude. \n\"\nI have a template that I work through, record a monologue while on a walk for about 60 minutes, then that monologue transcript, pipe it through Anthropic's Claude 3 Opus, use it as a thought partner, generate some key takeaways and actions, and then finally, if there's anything I really want to make sure I take to heart, I'll have Claude create song lyrics according to my intentions, and then create a catchy song with Suno.\n\"\nIt takes something like 20 iterations to get a really excellent output, but you can quickly scrub through each one and probably within a minute or so find the song that will really stick. \n\"\nI'm linking to an example below along with a recap of my key takeaways from the last time doing this earlier this week in the comments.\n\"\nhttps://lnkd.in/eCm5Seg3\n\"\nYou can also use this to prepare for upcoming meetings by imagining the best case scenario and developing a highly personalized and precise pump up track, or really whatever you want.\n\"\nOver 50% of my audio consumption at this point is Suno. I don't listen to music on Spotify really anymore and I consume podcasts primarily by pumping the transcripts through AI first to find the salient nuggets. \n\"\nLet me know if you have any questions about how to do this in the comments.\n\"\n\"(IMO the killer use case for AI-generated multimedia isn't entertainment but making sure information sticks and, at best, cultivating ordered desire toward business and personal goals.)",
