    "id": "post-2024-06-09-7205566273773027328",
    "title": "There's a lot of talk, talk, talk when it comes to generative AI",
    "date": "2024-06-09",
    "content": "There's a lot of talk, talk, talk when it comes to generative AI...\"\n\"\nHere's what you actually need to know:\n\"\nComputers have always been good at crunching numbers. Now they can crunch words, and they're getting better at it. \n\"\nSoon, they'll be able to handle raw audio, video, and other more exotic data.\n\"\nJust like you use Excel to perform functions on numbers, you can use large language models (LLMs) to process words. \n\"\nAnd, as the scope of what can be computed expands (numbers, words, etc.), so does the scope of what you can delegate to machines.\n\"\n‚è© The primary benefit you are afforded is neither cost nor quality but \"speed.\n\"\nOnce a computer can produce an output at a satisfying level of quality, you can delegate the creation of that output to an AI system. \n\"\nAlthough what the computer produces may ultimately be only on par with what you or somebody you would have hired would have produced, it's likely that the machine will do so 10‚Äì1,000 times faster.\n\"\n‚úÖ This means that certain tasks and subtasks (that previously took days or weeks) can now be completed in just minutes via prudent delegation to these word-crunching machines.\n\"\nüîÑ While not everything can be delegated, the aggregate impact of this process refactoring is a reduced overall cycle time.\n\"\nüéØ Thus, you can redirect surplus time and attention to taking action under conditions of uncertainty by pulling new desirable outcomes closer to the present. And at best, you are applying the same approach to helping your customers solve their goals.\n\"\nThis increased speed and flexibility opens up a solution space where you can not only experiment with technology but also new business models. \n\"\nInstead of being anchored to selling inputs (billable hours) or outputs (one-size-fits-all deliverables), you can now focus on selling against uncertain outcomes and charge accordingly.\n\"\nP.S:\n\"\n\"If you could wave a magic wand and do one thing a thousand times faster, what would it be?",
