    "date": "2024-06-07",
    "content": "I'm often asked about my favorite AI tools. And I usually say, \"Oh, I just use Claude and a meeting note taker.\" \"\n\"\nBut then I took an inventory and realized my cyborg toolkit has expanded substantially beyond those two. After another AI workshop - thanks Tyler Rossmaessler for hosting - I thought I'd share a sneak peek of what's in there.\n\"\nIn particular, I want to highlight three tools you may or may not have heard of.\n\"\nThe first is Figma. While it has some awesome AI functionality, I use it more as the primary surface for collaborating with clients. I've switched almost entirely from docs, slides, and sheets to collaborative digital whiteboards.\n\"\nThe second is an AI-powered sales tool called Clay. Ryan Markman is an expert and you should definitely follow him if you're interested in turbo-charging your sales and marketing folks with AI.\n\"\nAnd then last but not least, there's my recent favorite - Vapi (YC W21). It allows you to spin up custom-voiced agents that you can put behind phone numbers. I've been using it for everything from vetting contractors around the world, conducting asynchronous discovery interviews, and collecting feedback to improve proposal content with asynchronous review by experts. \n\"\nI really think the bespoke voice agent thing is going to be a game changer - something to pay attention to. \n\"\n\"What other tools would you add to this list?",
