    "date": "2024-05-11",
    "content": "You shouldn't expect AI to make all 1,000 of your employees 10% more productive in a year.\"\n\"\nYou should expect 10 of your employees to have already used AI to get stuff done 1,000x as fast as their peers.\n\"\nA top-down AI mandate + mandatory employee training is probably going to waste your money and their time.\n\"\nInstead, find the secret cyborgs in your organization.\n\"\nHelp them become role models who inspire their colleagues - who illustrates the astounding fact that things that were literally impossible a few months ago are now possible.\n\"\nRemember, you can't make anyone do what they don't want to, especially in the age of remote work. \n\"\nYour job as a chief executive is to reduce uncertainty on the frontier by setting good goals, investing in insight-yielding experiments, and elevating individuals who embody the values you want to encode into your company culture.\n\"\nTo turbo-charge this process, when you're ready, convene a cross-functional team of AI-powered pioneers and invest your political and financial capital in an expedition that has the potential to transform not only your company, but your entire industry.\n\"\nTowards that end, you can use OKRs + AI can help you focus on the frontier & accelerate.\n\"\n\"Send me a DM to learn how.",
