    "title": "How to repurpose long-form video content using AI: \"\n\" \"\n\"Long-form...",
    "date": "2024-05-07",
    "content": "How to repurpose long-form video content using AI: \"\n \nLong-form video content is a goldmine. \n \nYou could create: \n \n‚Ä¢ Blog posts \n‚Ä¢ Newsletters \n‚Ä¢ Linkedin articles \n‚Ä¢ Twitter threads \n \nNow, think of ChatGPT & Claude as 2 freelance writers. \n \nTo start, you can pick 1. \nTo take it to the next level, you can use both. \n \nI recently created blog post drafts using both under the supervision of an expert copywriter. \n \nAnd the results were impressive. \n \nHere‚Äôs the process I used: \n \n1. I generated transcripts of videos using Descript \n2. I provided the transcript to both AI systems and asked them to write a blog post on a given topic. \n     \n(Copywriter‚Äôs feedback: \n \nChatGPT is good with ‚ÄúStructuring‚Äù the content. \nClaude is good with ‚ÄúStyling‚Äù the content. \n \nSo, I continued...) \n \n3. I asked ChatGPT to give me the structure. \n4. I gave the structure to Claude and asked for a rewrite. \n5. Finally, I asked the expert to record feedback and gave it to Claude for final iteration. \n \nNote how this is exactly like working with 2 writers. \n \nWe take both writer‚Äôs drafts and pick the best parts from both. \n \nIn the end, the blog post generated was quite good. \n \nIf you have a lot of video content available, \n \nYou can use this process to generate good 1st drafts. (at scale) \n \nTry it out! \n \nAnd let me know how it goes. \n \n*** \n \nPS ‚Äì If you want to test out such AI-assisted content systems, I have 1 FREE slot still open for my AI-power hour calls. \n \nIn the call, we‚Äôll: \n \n‚Ä¢ Assess the highest leverage AI opportunity \n‚Ä¢ Build a prototype solution \n‚Ä¢ Create a roadmap for AI integration \n \n\"DM me ‚ÄúAI coach‚Äù if you wanna get started!",
