    "title": "Valuable skills are transferable",
    "date": "2024-05-02",
    "content": "Valuable skills are transferable.\"\n\"\nOctober 2022: I faced one of the toughest transitions of my life.\n\"\nShutting down my startup ‚Üí Becoming an Indie consultant\n\"\nMy co-founder and I had poured 2 years of our lives into the startup.\nTime, money, and an unbelievable amount of energy.\n\"\nTo shut it down was soul-crushing.\n\"\nFor 36 hours, I had a pity-party.\nI questioned everything, felt horrible, and even pessimistic at times.\n\"\nBut then, a wave of realizations hit me:\n\"\nIt had positives to look at.\n\"\n‚Ä¢ I had developed valuable skills in the process (OKRs)\n‚Ä¢ I had demonstrated value-creation in a complex market\n‚Ä¢ I had built strong connections in the industry\n\"\nAnd this got me back up!\n\"\nI connected with one of my business connections and got my first deal as an OKR consultant.\n\"\nSince then, over 14 months, I‚Äôve worked with 20+ clients through my solo independent boutique consultancy GSD @ Work.\n\"\nAnd consistently,\n\"\nI‚Äôve noticed how the skills I learned have transferred into this next phase.\n\"\nNot only am I happy about the bets I‚Äôve made, \nBut I‚Äôm also enjoying the flexibility that comes with this mode of business.\n\"\nIn the end, \n\"\nOne lesson stands out for me!\nSomething I‚Äôd repeatedly want to tell myself.\n\"\nAttempting to solve a difficult problem you are intrinsically motivated to solve never goes to waste.\n\"\nWe had set out to transform the entire mental health profession.\n\"\nThe challenge was big. But we were mission-driven, high-energy & determined to make a difference.\n\"\nOn the journey, battling all the problems that came our way, we developed processes and systems that are valuable to the market.\n\"\nThose same systems help me solve different problems elsewhere through my indie agency GSD @ work.\n\"\nLooking back, I‚Äôm proud of the value we created.\n\"\nAnd the decisions we took.\n\"\nWhole-hearted attempts at value creation always reward you.\n\"\nThere's immense power in resilience.\n\"\n\"And sometimes, a closed door leads to paths we never imagined :)",
