    "date": "2024-04-30",
    "content": "How I use AI on mobile to speed up communication: \"\n \n(And generate high-quality responses for emails & notifications) \n \n1. I open my inbox. \n2. I open the first email. \n3. I read the email & collect my thoughts. \n4. I open my AI transcriber (rec: Loom) \n5. I dictate my answer as if I‚Äôm in a conversation \n6. I go to Claude/ChatGPT and use this prompt \n \n‚ÄùHey ChatGPT, please add whitespaces and line breaks to make this text readable for me‚Äù \n \n(Note: You can skip this step if you use Superwhisper. It has this functionality inbuilt) \n \n7. I edit the final response for accuracy \n8. I hit send  \n9. I move to my notifications (Linkedin/ Slack) & repeat \n \nI do this once every evening before logging off. \n \nAmong all *daily* use-cases of AI, I‚Äôve found this to be super helpful. \n \nMy productivity has skyrocketed. \n \nHere‚Äôs a rough estimate ‚Üì \n \nAs a startup founder, I used to take 2-3 hours to clear my inbox. \n \nNow, on average, it takes me 5-10 mins (!) to do the same. \n \nYes, it works that fast. \n \nSince it‚Äôs conversational, my replies are better. \n \nAnd since it‚Äôs simple, it gives me time to think my answers through. \n \nA game changer. \n \n\"Would recommend you try it out!",
