    "content": "The nature of \"the firm\" may fundamentally change due to AI.\"\n\"\nUnderstanding how (e.g., information and labor liquidity) + why (e.g., lower transaction costs, power law‚Äìdistributed global talent) could be critical for c-suite leaders who want to survive and thrive.\n\"\nNeither incumbents nor new entrants necessarily have a natural advantage in this regard. \n\"\nIt may simply come down to decisively and proactively using new (largely managerial) capabilities as fuel to accelerate forward progress on the frontier ‚Äî and this would be an opportunity that is open to everyone, regardless of industry or company size.\n\"\n(Details from a Claude‚Äìsummarized morning monologue starting to think this through in the screenshots.)\n\"\nWill the fundamental nature of the firm change due to AI? \n\"\nWill we see waves of innovation in corporate formation and management practices in the 2020s and beyond? \n\"\n\"Share your thoughts in the comments!",
