    "content": "Initially, I found remote work excruciating.  \"\n \nBut now, 4 years later, I‚Äôm convinced it‚Äôs more effective than in-person office work.  \n \nHere are 4 reasons why: \n \n1/ Employees get the freedom to design their schedules. \n‚Ü≥ Happy employees do great work. \n \n2/ Remote work enforces discipline. \n‚Ü≥ If there are skill/fit/performance issues, they get revealed very quickly. \n \n3/ Async communication creates a private information repository \n‚Ü≥ When you create Loom videos, you‚Äôre building your goldmine of information, on autopilot! \n \n(Recording yourself in an office doesn‚Äôt seem right)  \n \n4/ Allows global collaboration \n‚Ü≥ You can find high-energy, smart people specializing in your industry & problems. \n \nEspecially after the advent of generative AI: \n \nThe advantages of the remote mode of work have outsized the traditional ways. \n \nOpportunity for more flexibility. \nOpportunity for more resources. \nOpportunity for more accountability. \nOpportunity for more control over your life! \n \nAnd with zero additional effort,  \n \nYou start building your data asset. \n \nSo, even if remote work started as a painful necessity, I think it‚Äôs here to stay! \n \nAnd it‚Äôs only just getting started. \n \n\"What are your thoughts?",
