    "id": "post-2024-04-22-7188162803004755969",
    "title": "Before you, an ambitious CEO, commit to a quarterly strategic direc...",
    "date": "2024-04-22",
    "content": "Before you, an ambitious CEO, commit to a quarterly strategic direction, it's critical that you've gathered sufficient high-quality information to inform the goal-setting process.\"\n\"\nI've found 5 questions to be particularly potent, so I make sure they're answered by all stakeholders (the executive team at least, and ideally the entire company, either during live interviews or asynchronously via a service like Voiceform or Vapi (YC W21)) prior to our all-day objective-setting workshop.\n\"\nThey are:\n\"\n1. \"The Bayesian\": How confident are you, from 1‚Äì99%, that [your company] will [accomplish its specified mission] by [1, 5, or 10 years]? What would have to be true for your answer to be [20% higher]? And why wasn't it [20% lower]?\n\"\n2. \"The pre-mortem\": If [your company] fails to [achieve its mission], why would that have been the case?\n\"\n3. \"The Peter Thiel question\": What is one thing you know to be true about [your company/the industry] that few other people at [your company] would agree with you on?\n\"\n4. \"The battery question\": Over the past three months, can you think of a single time you felt most energized? And then a time you felt most drained?\n\"\n5. \"The surplus quantifier\": If I were to wave a magic wand and take all of the [energy-draining tasks] off your plate, and you could reinvest all that surplus time and attention into [energy-giving tasks], how would that feel? And, assuming I could snap my fingers and make this 100% a reality, today, what would be an offensive amount of money for me to ask for?\n\"\nAll, and especially the first three, inform strategy and direction-setting. The last two can also help you understand where you're likely to get the biggest boost from generative AI, since energy-draining tasks that need to get done, your team knows how to do, but no one really wants to do can be prudently delegated to word-crunching machines.\n\"\nBring it all together to, during that critical all-day workshop, focus on the frontier & contemplate¬†‚Äî¬†and then during the quarter: delegate, orchestrate, and accelerate.\n\"\n\"What other questions would you add to the 5 above?",
