    "id": "post-2024-04-19-7187087557455753219",
    "title": "AI's capabilities are growing",
    "date": "2024-04-19",
    "content": "AI's capabilities are growing. \"\n \nPushing beyond simple tasks into the realm of innovation.  \n \nWhen ChatGPT was released, it could only be used one way. \n \nYou could ask it questions, and get interesting answers. \nBut you couldn‚Äôt rely on it for a fruitful conversation. \n \nToday, ChatGPT is a different weapon. \n \nYou can instruct it to become a serious thought partner. \nTo ask you questions to refine your thinking. \n \nAnd it becomes a creativity assistant! \n \nThink about this for a moment. \n \nThis signals a shift in the way we‚Äôll work. \n \n1/ Humans are freed from mundane tasks. \n2/ Humans also can quickly refine their ideas. \n \nCombined, it signals an era of (possibly) unprecedented innovation and breakneck speeds. \n \nThe verdict, to me, is simple: \n \nThe sooner we build healthy relationships with AI-enhanced media, the sooner we'll cultivate the necessary skills and intuition for its most beneficial use. \n \nSo, start experimenting with AI today. \n \nIt doesn‚Äôt matter how small (or even trivial) the task is. \n \n\"As I tell all my clients, ‚ÄúIt only takes one AHA moment to unlock a completely new world‚Äù.",
