    "title": "IMO Gemini 1",
    "date": "2024-04-10",
    "content": "IMO Gemini 1.5 via the AI Studio is, IMO, a v0.8 agentic system.\"\n\"\nThe multimodality (true audio, video, and text) allow you to do incredible things. \n\"\nI've been, frankly disappointed thus far in Google's performance in the AI race, but I can say they definitively have some advantages with this latest release, at least for now.\n\"\nTo get a sense of what I'm talking about, record a long form Loom\n video where you're explaining to someone in-depth how to do something, including by showing them with lots of switching across applications, etc., and then simply pop the video into Gemini 1.5 without a text prompt. \n\"\nIt will take a few minutes to process (hence the \"agentic AI\" feeling of asynchronously delegating a meaty task), and I think you'll be surprised by the output.\n\"\n\"The space between high-quality information (e.g., 60-minute Loom recording) and knowledge (e.g., SOP), and then knowledge and capital asset (e.g., code) just got a whole lot smaller.",
