    "id": "post-2024-03-21-7176584908671246337",
    "title": "So, a use case I want to share that will work especially well if yo...",
    "date": "2024-03-21",
    "content": "So, a use case I want to share that will work especially well if you have an Anthropic Claude Pro account and can use Claude 3 Opus is in-person networking event preparation. \"\n\"\nDoing this is pretty simple. If you have a guest list and depending on the event platform, that's usually publicly available, you can simply go through every single person's name on the list, find their LinkedIn profile, and mindlessly copy and paste it all into a TXT file. \n\"\nThen, upload it to Claude, use an app like superwhisper to just ramble and dictate a bit about what your goals are, what your background is, and whatever context you might want to give to an analyst to whom you delegate this sort of research and preparation task, and then hit enter. \n\"\nSee if Claude can give you basically two outputs. One is the general makeup of attendees and two would be three to five individuals from the entire list that it thinks you should prioritize building relationships with, along with its reasoning. \n\"\nThen, do more research, read those LinkedIn profiles closely, turn SuperWhisper back on, and just ramble and dictate your thoughts aloud per person. If they've been on podcast episodes or long form YouTube video interviews, you can take the transcripts from those and stuff them into Claude as well, and then finish dictating. \n\"\nGo back-and-forth with Claude until you're satisfied, and then ask it to compile all of that into a brief memo per person that you can refer back to on the drive to the event or right before. \n\"\nDo this for those top three to five people and glance at the summaries that Claude created for the rest, and I guarantee you'll have a significantly more fruitful time. \n\"\n\"And this all can be done in say 15 to 20 minutes, but would have been prohibitively expensive before and necessitated a team of analysts or researchers who would have taken much longer.",
