    "date": "2024-03-19",
    "content": "Worried robots are coming for your job?\"\n\"\nThink again...\n\"\nLet's take lawyers for example:\n\"\nAI will enable innovation in corporate formation and contracting as the limiting factor of attention and intelligence is removed.\n\"\n(LLMs are just computers that can crunch words.)\n\"\nJevon's paradox (more overall spend on something as prices decline) will apply not only to software, but also legal work.\n\"\nLawyers & software engineers (and probably doctors) will not only be just fine, but also in greater demand, assuming they can stick the landing to new business models that charge for outcomes, not inputs.\n\"\nThe particulars of the work and how it gets done will change, but I expect there to be more demand for professional services per se.\n\"\n\"Best way to prepare is to start experimenting with tools like Claude Pro on a daily basis!",
