    "title": "14 harsh realities about AI \"\n\" \"\n\"No AI influencer talks about the...",
    "date": "2024-03-06",
    "content": "14 harsh realities about AI \"\n \nNo AI influencer talks about these: \n \n1/ Crafting effective ChatGPT prompts is an art \n‚Ü≥ It's about gathering the right info, not just using convoluted, pre-baked prompts. \n \n2/ AI is transformative, but not overnight magic \n‚Ü≥ It feels magical but requires strategic organizational blueprinting to truly change the game. \n \n3/ Strategic AI investments are key \n‚Ü≥ Focus on deep, narrow bets in areas where you already have an edge, rather than a scattershot approach. \n \n4/ AI recommendations need a balanced approach \n‚Ü≥ Be open to AI's potential but always verify its suggestions through testing and experimentation. \n \n5/ Narrow AI focus yields bigger impact \n‚Ü≥ Ambitious goals with tight constraints and limited scope are more likely to lead to significant outcomes. \n \n6/ Boasting about AI use is not enough \n‚Ü≥ Real value is found in tangible improvements in quality and speed, not just using AI because it‚Äôs cool - AI as means, not an end :) \n \n7/ AI can't replace human-led storytelling or courageous action on the frontier \n‚Ü≥ AI assists in discovery and problem-solving but doesn't replace the need for prudent human action under conditions of radical uncertainty. \n \n8/ AI use in customer service requires an even more human touch \n‚Ü≥ Empower customer service reps with AI tools for efficiency, but stress the primary importance of human empathy and connection. \n \n9/ Embrace AI for future career growth \n‚Ü≥ AI is here to stay! \n \n10/ AI integration and upskilling go hand in hand \n‚Ü≥ The best results come from first meeting people where they are, with targeted training and support, freeing employees up to discover their strengths and take things to a whole new level \n \n11/ AI enhances but doesn't replace creativity \n‚Ü≥ Use AI as an on-ramp to quality that helps human users achieve intense focus where their attention adds the most value. \n \n12/ AI for innovation, not just cost-cutting \n‚Ü≥ Redirect time and resources saved by AI into new opportunities and revenue streams with asymmetric upside. \n \n13/ Strategic AI use accelerates the pursuit of good goals  \n‚Ü≥ Align AI with strategic goals for the greatest impact, always prioritizing the good of your customer. \n \n14/ AI + long-term vision can yield short-term results \n‚Ü≥ Choose the low-hanging fruit for AI in the context of long-term goals. Gives outsized value in the present and opens interesting opportunities for the future \n \nAI has the potential to make people 10x more effective \n. \nBut 99% are doing it wrong ‚Üí and that's what I'm on a mission to solve \n \nREPOST ‚ôªÔ∏è If you wish you knew this sooner \n \n\"PS - What would you add?",
