    "title": "My 4 step framework that helps me uncover actionable AI use cases f...",
    "date": "2024-02-29",
    "content": "My 4 step framework that helps me uncover actionable AI use cases for my clients: \"\n \n1/ Get clarity on the Goals \n \nAsk the question: ‚ÄúIf we could wave a magic wand and achieve one major result in 3 months, what would it be?\" \nGoals set context for AI integration.  \nOnce we know where we‚Äôre trying to go, AI then becomes a means by which we get there 10x faster. \n \n2/ Business Blueprinting \n \nDraw an end-to-end map of the company's processes. I use Miro for this. \nOnce we have a visual representation of the company‚Äôs workflows, AI opportunities start jumping out.  \nEspecially since we‚Äôve clarified what‚Äôs the goal we‚Äôre trying to achieve! \n \n3/ Identify AI-integration opportunities \n \nDig out pain points where AI can effectively eliminate bottlenecks. \nI‚Äôve found 2 lenses to be very effective: \n‚Ü≥ How can we use AI to streamline operations? \n‚Ü≥ How can we use AI to drive innovation? \nIf done right, operators buy back time and start working more on energizing activities, delegating draining work to our friendly AI assistants. \n \n4/ Find the Champion \n \nAssign the role of AI Champion to an enthusiastic early adopter. \nFuel their desire to master the craft of AI by giving them the license to experiment.  \nAsk them to present their findings in check-in meetings. \nNot only does the champion upskill, but this kick-starts the AI culture within the organization. \n \n*** \n \nMy aim with my clients is to guide them to their first ‚ÄúAHA‚Äù moment with AI. \n \nBecause that‚Äôs all it takes. \nOnce they experience the way of working with AI, they never go back! \n \nWhat do you think? \n \n\"Have you had your first ‚ÄúAHA‚Äù moment yet?",
