    "id": "post-2024-02-27-7168243515842363392",
    "title": "Step zero to powering up your business with AI:\"\n\"\"\n\"Start recordin...",
    "date": "2024-02-27",
    "content": "Step zero to powering up your business with AI:\"\n\"\nStart recording everything**\n\"\nData is the new oil.\nMost of your interactions are data (raw materials) that you can turn into an asset.\n\"\nWhy now? \nComputers used to only be able to crunch numbers; now they can crunch words (and, soon, images, video and audio).\n\"\nThis includes:\n‚Üí Review meetings\n‚Üí Brainstorming sessions\n‚Üí Sales calls\n‚Üí Client conversations.\n\"\nAll this data has huge potential that we can use AI to tap into.\nDon‚Äôt let this powerful raw material go to waste.\n\"\nStart recording!\n\"\nI recommend 2 tools:\n\"\n1/ Scribe by Vienna Hypertext (For iPhone users)\nPersonal thoughts are valuable if you learn to use them.\nWhenever you feel heavy with information, turn on Scribe & speak out your thoughts.\nRaw, unstructured is awesome. We don‚Äôt need it to be perfect!\n\"\n2/ Read AI or Otter.ai (For Teams)\nBoth apps are AI notetakers.\nThey‚Äôll join your meetings, transcribe them & give you detailed notes (summary, insights & takeaways).\nMany of my clients have been surprised at how valuable these tools have turned out to be.\n\"\nWith this, you build your Private Digital Memory.\nAnd this Private Digital Memory becomes your personal goldmine!\n\"\nOver time, TONS of unexpected opportunities & solutions start revealing themselves.\n\"\nNew ideas, marketing materials, decision diaries, strategies, and systems.\nThe goldmine has everything!\n\"\nAnd with AI set to become more powerful every single day, this is how we future-proof ourselves.\n\"\n\"\n**Always follow recording consent laws, at the federal and state levels. \n\"\nAsk for permission, share recordings with all participants, and adhere to both legal requirements and social norms.\n\"\nEnsure information security and privacy with practices like multi-factor authentication, maintaining strict control and security over your Private Digital Memory.\n\"\n\"It's essential, yet often goes unsaid :)",
