    "date": "2024-02-16",
    "content": "How can you improve the quality of your conversations with AI? \"\n \n(Especially effective for Coaches & Consultants) \n \nFirstly, let‚Äôs look at what makes a coaching conversation effective: \n‚Üí Did you ask the right questions? \n‚Üí Did you correctly identify the bottleneck? \n‚Üí Did you get specific information that helps you make progress? \n \nAll this happens when you‚Äôve researched and come prepared for the call. \nBut doing this takes time for every client. \nThat‚Äôs where AI comes in! \n \nSo before we start using AI, we must clarify the goal. \n \nGoal: To use AI to prepare better & faster for coaching conversations \nHere‚Äôs the solution I propose: \n \nStep 1) Gather Context \n \nYou need to collect 3 types of information: \n \nPublic info ‚Üí Social Media content, Youtube transcripts, Blogs, etc. \nPrivate info ‚Üí Transcripts from your previously recorded conversations \nDictated context ‚Üí A transcript of your thoughts on current context (goals, concerns, caveats, any other information) \n \nIf you haven‚Äôt already, I recommend Read AI for recording conversations & Superwhisper for dictated context. \n \nStep 2) Prepare with Claude \n \nOpen Claude & supply it with all this information. \n \nAnd then just ask claude an open-ended question: \n‚ÄúI have this client meeting coming up in 20 minutes. Help me prepare.‚Äù \nNow Claude will go through the tons of information and suggest you tailored plans. \n \nI‚Äôve seen 90-95% times, it gives pretty amazing results. \nRemember: Don‚Äôt expect magic. Expect nuggets of insights to help you think. \n \nWork with AI to design an effective conversation. \n \nStep 3) Iterate better with Claude \n \nOnce done, paste the transcript from the call in the same Claude window. \n \nThen again ask claude an open-ended question: \n‚ÄúThis is how the meeting went. Can you tell me what I could have improved?‚Äù \n \nMake AI your trusted advisor. \nWorking with it, you can significantly improve your speeds of iterations. \n \nThat‚Äôs it! \nKeep following the process & you‚Äôll see how you‚Äôll become 10x more effective over time! \n \n*** \nPS ‚Äì We covered this during a live AI power hour a few weeks ago with Lapo Lazzati, Mike Newton & Nick Pope. \n \nOver a 60-minute call, we discussed applications of AI across a variety of domains. \n \nHere‚Äôs a video from the live session explaining the same concept üëáüèª \n\"",
