    "title": "Most business owners misunderstand AI",
    "date": "2024-02-05",
    "content": "Most business owners misunderstand AI. \"\n \nAI isn't about automating jobs. \n \nIt's about augmenting human capabilities. \n \nIf you're integrating AI into your business, here's what effective use of AI takes into account: \n \n1) Your overarching goal \n‚Ü≥ How clearly do you understand your direction? \n \n2) Deconstructing the goal into tasks \n‚Ü≥ How clearly do you understand your ‚Äòjobs to be done‚Äù (and how they‚Äôre done now!)? \n \n3) Selectively delegating tasks to AI  \n‚Ü≥ How much time can you buy back by effectively using technology? \n \n4) Using the time to become productive & feel energized \n‚Ü≥ How creatively can you use the time to build relationships & drive innovation? \n \nBecoming AI-powered forces you to upskill in all 4 areas. \n \nAnd as you become better, AI becomes more powerful. \n \nResult -> A flywheel that helps you achieve your goals 10x faster! \n \nDon‚Äôt think about AI as a tool for cutting corners. \nAI is a catalyst for enhancing productivity. \n \nLet's not let old misconceptions hold us back. \nRemember, the true value of AI lies in its impact on people, not the technology itself. \n \nI think it's time we start embracing this new way of working. \nAnd witness the transformation it can bring to our businesses. \n \n\"Transforming the way we work and the way we live.",
