    "id": "post-2024-01-23-7155559962805477376",
    "title": "I like playing the game of Entrepreneurship on Hard mode",
    "date": "2024-01-23",
    "content": "I like playing the game of Entrepreneurship on Hard mode. \"\n \nValue >>> everything else. \n \nHere‚Äôs how I design my client engagements: \n \nùü≠/ ùó¶ùó∞ùóºùóΩùó≤ ùóÆ ùóΩùóøùóºùóØùóπùó≤ùó∫, ùó£ùó∂ùòÅùó∞ùóµ ùóÆ ùòÄùóºùóπùòÇùòÅùó∂ùóºùóª \n \nBeginning of every client engagement, I present a slide with 4 titles. \n‚Üí Outcomes (What are we trying to achieve?) \n‚Üí Outputs (What will you get at the end?) \n‚Üí Agenda (How will we get there?) \n‚Üí Time (How much time will it take?) \n \nFor Example: \n \nHere‚Äôs how I structured one of my 2-hour ‚ÄúIntroduction to AI‚Äù paid consulting projects: \n \n(The client was curious about how they could use AI to power up their business) \n \nOutcome ‚Üí XXX team makes meaningful progress on a strategic objective by using AI to create a deliverable and/or increase process efficiency AND, as a consequence, participants gain confidence that they‚Äôll use AI to become more productive over the next 3 months \n \nOutputs ‚Üí Recordings, transcripts, scratch pad, code (a mini software) \n \nAgenda & Time‚Üí \nIntro [5 mins] \nAI toolkit overview: Landscape with capabilities and caveats [10 mins] \nSizzler [10 mins] \nDeep-Dive: Building a mini custom AI software to solve a specific problem [90 mins] \nRecap + next steps [10 mins] \n \nThis helps both me & client have extreme clarity about everything we‚Äôre doing together. \n \n \nùüÆ/ ùóñùóÆùòÄùóµ ùòÇùóΩùó≥ùóøùóºùóªùòÅ ùòÑùó∂ùòÅùóµ ùó¶ùóÆùòÅùó∂ùòÄùó≥ùóÆùó∞ùòÅùó∂ùóºùóª ùóöùòÇùóÆùóøùóÆùóªùòÅùó≤ùó≤ \n \nThe handshake deal with clients is: \n‚ÄúAt any point in time, if you do not feel I‚Äôm providing the value I promised, you can call off the engagement and I‚Äôll give you a pro-rated refund. No questions asked.‚Äù \n \nThis unlocks 3 benefits: \n1. Cash upfront forces both parties to become focused on the outcome. \n‚Ü≥ An investment makes you invested in the result. Hence, we move 10x faster. \n \n2. Satisfaction Guarantee forces me to be confident in the results I deliver \n‚Ü≥ If I‚Äôm unsure about my skills/ability to deliver, I won‚Äôt make the pitch to begin with! \n \n3. I take up Zero outside funds to run the business \n‚Ü≥ After shutting down my equity-financed startup, I‚Äôve made profitability the North Star. \n \n \nPlaying the game on hard mode forces me to up-skill as an entrepreneur with every new client engagement. \n \n \nYes, it‚Äôs not easy, and sometimes feels like I am taking it to extremes. \nBut it has been a fantastic catalyst for my learning, especially with generative AI. \n \nThe constraints help me unlock the creativity required to push the boundaries of what's possible with a brand-new technology. (without wasting my or client‚Äôs time) \n \n \nAnd, last but not least,  this mode of Entrepreneurship has unlocked a beautiful freedom that allows me to work on my interests and earn a living while doing so. \n \nTruly grateful and truly excited for everything to come :) \n\"",
    "excerpt": "I like playing the game of Entrepreneurship on Hard mode. \" \" \" \"Value >>> everything else. \" \" \" \"Here‚Äôs how I design my client engagements: \" \" \" \"ùü≠/...",
