    "title": "11 things that destroy AI effectiveness: \"\n\" \"\n\"1",
    "date": "2024-01-16",
    "content": "11 things that destroy AI effectiveness: \"\n \n1. Thinking ‚Äú100 ChatGPT prompts‚Äù will help you become AI-Powered \n \n2. Directionless AI adoption without clear linking to business goals \n \n3. Inadequate process articulation & poor quality input data  \n \n4. Expecting immediate impact without a learning curve \n \n5. Not enough feedback cycles to train AI properly \n \n6. Poor change management while introducing AI \n \n7. Making AI a substitute for human creativity \n \n8. Believing in one-size-fits-all AI solutions \n \n9. Blaming AI‚Äôs limitations for bad results \n \n10. Scaling too quickly \n \n11. No patience \n \nAvoid these at all costs. \n \n\"Did I miss out on anything?",
