    "title": "3 Tips to become an AI-powered business owner without heavily alter...",
    "date": "2024-01-12",
    "content": "3 Tips to become an AI-powered business owner without heavily altering your existing workflows: \"\n \n1Ô∏è‚É£¬†Stop typing and start talking.  \n \nSwitch to dictating communications instead of typing whenever possible.  \n \nThis allows you to communicate 3x faster, with higher quality output.  \n \nUse Scribe, the ChatGPT app with Whisper, or Super-Whisper to dictate emails, documents, and social media posts. \n \nThe dictation-enabled increase in throughput and your newfound ability to iterate through more feedback cycles will lead to overall better results. \n \n \n2Ô∏è‚É£¬†Record everything to enable asynchronous communication.  \n \nUse tools like Descript & Otter to record processes and meetings with automatically generated transcripts.  \n \nYou can then use AI to extract tailored information from the raw recordings. \n \nThis reduces friction for remote team communication - And your team can work *much* more flexibly (and on their own terms). \n \n \n3Ô∏è‚É£¬†Integrate AI capabilities into existing tools over adding new ones.  \n \nFor example, build a Slack bot that connects to AI models through Zapier. \n \nOr use a simple web app interface to abstract away complex AI configurations.  \n \nThis makes adoption frictionless by meeting people's existing workflows. \n \n*** \n \nThe key is that all these little boosts compound. \n \nEach change is small. But over time, the impact on team efficiency and velocity is enormous. \n \n \nSo, try them out.  \n \n\"You‚Äôll be surprised to see how well it works!",
