    "date": "2024-01-08",
    "content": "üò£ My 5 biggest struggles as a beginner independent AI consultant were: \"\n \n1. Moving on from my previous startup (that I poured my heart and soul into for 2 years) \n \n2. Lacking technical skills in coding to build and deploy custom applications without an engineering team \n \n3. Communicating what AI is and how it can create value in an understandable way \n \n4. Adapting AI innovations to the practical (and diverse) needs of clients \n \n5. Getting too comfortable working remotely and not prioritizing in-person networking \n \n \nüìå Anyone who's starting out as an indie AI consultant, here's some wisdom I wish I would have known: \n \n1. Accept the shift with a growth mindset. Yes, it‚Äôs not easy to dive into something new, but it‚Äôs also the most exciting path forward. \n \n2. Delegate extensively to AI and find talented humans globally to complement your skills \n \n3. Specificity is key. Focus on solving small but real problems for clients. As soon as they get their first ‚ÄúAha!‚Äù moment with AI, they‚Äôll never go back. \n \n4. Stay curious and keep studying AI deeply. Over time, you‚Äôll start identifying creative solutions for various client problems and noticing general patterns that make you more efficient with each engagement. \n \n5. Invest your attention and energy into high-quality in-person events to build meaningful relationships and grow your professional network. Less is more in this regard: fewer events with greater preparation; coming up with a plan beforehand can make a huge difference. It takes only one new meaningful connection to make attending an event worth it!  \n \n \n \nAlmost a year into the journey, I‚Äôm super excited about all the possibilities that await the lives of other indie consultants using cutting-edge technology to help business owners worldwide. \n \nA future where AI & humans collaborate seamlessly would truly be beautiful. \n \nAnd we‚Äôre building the future one client at a time :) \n \n \n \nüîë Are you struggling with any other specific problems?  \n \n\"I'm happy to share more of my experience.",
