    "id": "post-2023-12-22-7144019565318926336",
    "title": "The internet has already liberated workers from the constraints of ...",
    "date": "2023-12-22",
    "content": "The internet has already liberated workers from the constraints of the first three dimensions. AI frees us from the fourth.\"\n\"\nToday, if a knowledge worker has a question that necessitates rote information retrieval at the very least, and perhaps some analysis or cognition sprinkled on top, they have two options if they're remote.\n\"\nThe first is to command F, so to speak, through company documentation, and that takes time (if they can even find the correct information); then, they have to synthesize it into something useful to solve the problem at hand.\n\"\nThe second is to send a message to a manager, who they've identified as likely to have access to the desired information.\n\"\nNow, one can imagine that if companies had proprietary AI models (or maybe fine-tuned foundation model endpoints) trained on their proprietary data, all of that information‚Äîand the machine cognition sprinkled on top‚Äîcould be made directly available to the remote worker in a way that's highly personalized and immediately actionable.\n\"\nIn 2024, we'll see a wave of professional AI copilot products. The chat-and-autocomplete experience of GitHub's Copilot is boosting productivity for developers globally; we should expect similar applications in other professions.\n\"\nModels trained on (and with permissioned access to) niche corporate data that would make, at best, the tacit knowledge embedded in meeting recordings and transcripts, documentation, and whatever other primary sources that get digitized available to remote workers, available in a way that's significantly more valuable and accessible, especially versus the usual \"ask your manager\" approach.\n\"\nFor a growing number of tasks, workers will be able to get stuff done without needing to loop in their managers (importantly, for complex problem solving); thus, AI makes remote, ASYNCHRONOUS work more feasible, thereby lowering the barriers, not only of space but time as well, enabling high-quality, rapid, global collaboration between workers in ways that have never before been possible.\n\"\n\"As an independent consultant who serves clients across three continents and collaborates with AI-armed developers and marketers across two more, I couldn't be more excited about what's ahead.",
