    "title": "How AI is Making my Meetings More Human:\"\n\"\"\n\"I've been experimenti...",
    "date": "2023-12-13",
    "content": "How AI is Making my Meetings More Human:\"\n\"\nI've been experimenting with some interesting use cases for Anthropic's Claude AI assistant that have shown promising early results for improving meetings and relationships. \n\"\nBy spending 15 minutes before each meeting dumping relevant context and history (e.g., their LI profile, previous meeting notes, transcripts from recent podcast interviews) into Claude, it can help me prepare by surfacing key talking points, insights into what the other person might care most about, and hypotheses for making the discussion productive. With Claude's synthesis abilities, I can focus on strategy rather than information gathering and work with it as an AI thought partner to make the most of our time.\n\"\nAfter meetings, I paste the transcript from Otter.ai into Claude and have an insightful dialogue about how I might be able to help the other person in a spirit of charity. Claude's outside perspective often brings up things I may have missed and gives specific suggestions that I use to either take action or reach out to individuals in my network who'd be better able help; quick turnaround leads to immediate value and stronger professional relationships.\n\"\nWhile some view AI cynically as leading to spammy impersonal interactions, I believe the appropriate use of tools like Claude does the opposite - it can be used to elevate the quality of each conversation to be more thoughtful, constructive, and human by helping focus on what actually matters.\n\"\nPreparation and follow-up are enhanced rather than replaced. And Claude's knowledge and analysis make me better at understanding relationships, not worse. Our machines can make us more human when used collaboratively in this way.\n\"\n\"What do you think? Could AI like Claude help you have more meaningful dialogues if applied judiciously? I'd be curious to hear your perspectives!",
