    "title": "One big false belief I see among knowledge workers is, ‚ÄúAI will tak...",
    "date": "2023-11-28",
    "content": "One big false belief I see among knowledge workers is, ‚ÄúAI will take away my job‚Äù. \"\n \nThat‚Äôs NOT true. Here‚Äôs how I think about this ‚Üí \n \nAI will not replace you. \n \nBut, with AI as your sidekick, you might buy back 50-80% of your time. \n \n \nü§î Imagine this: \n \nA recent graduate of a master's degree program volunteers to work for you. \n \nThey work 24*7 and never complain. \n \nAnd while they‚Äôre a hard worker, they‚Äôre also a bit na√Øve! \n \n \nüßëüèª‚Äçüíª Now, when you start your day: \n \nYou can delegate half of the tasks on your to-do list to your assistant. \n \nAnd they‚Äôll never be upset when you delegate more things that you don‚Äôt want to do. \n \nWon‚Äôt you be happy to have someone like that working for you (and nearly for free)? \n \n \nüëâüèª The truth is: \n \nThere's an art and science to working with AI. \n \n- AI won‚Äôt do everything that you want to do \n- AI won‚Äôt do everything that you DON‚ÄôT want to do either \n \nIt really is like a recently graduated master‚Äôs student who‚Äôs eager to please. \n \n \nüôÅ But it‚Äôll make mistakes. You‚Äôll need to check it‚Äôs work. \n \nOver time,  \n \nYou‚Äôll learn to delegate higher proportions of support tasks that come bundled with your job.  \n \nSo that you free up more time to achieve higher levels of mastery in things that energize you. \n \n \nüí° That‚Äôs the actual goal. Isn‚Äôt it? \n \n \nAI won‚Äôt take away your job.  \n \nAI will make you more effective.  \n \nBut you‚Äôll have to learn the art and science of working with AI. \n \nAnd like any positive change, this will take time :) \n \nSo, if you‚Äôve been *secretly* putting off AI for a while, take this as your trigger to start today! \n \n*** \n \nP.S ‚Äì If you don‚Äôt know where to start, I‚Äôve built an AI crash course just for you! \n \nThis email course gives you everything you need to install AI and start using it confidently. \n \nThe course launches on Friday (2 days to go!). \n \n\"Comment ‚ÄúAI Electricity‚Äù and I‚Äôll add you to the waitlist!",
