    "date": "2023-11-21",
    "content": "Last week, I had a great conversation with Neil Chudleigh, founder of superwhisper, which has become an invaluable tool in my AI toolkit.\"\n\"\nIf you want to get instant value with AI (and set yourself up for long-term success), I'd recommend doing 3 things:\n\"\n1. Get your hands dirty! You don't need to spend a lot of time watching YouTube videos or scrolling Twitter (or LinkedIn for that matter) to understand what AI is and how it can be valuable to you; simply open Claude or ChatGPT and start telling the computer what you want it to do. Don't be afraid to ask for seemingly ridiculous things. You might be surprised at what's possible.\n\"\n2. Start creating a private store of digital memories, with, e.g., Rewind AI or Otter.ai, which you can use as raw material to work with via AI.\n\"\n\"3. Stop typing and start talking ‚Äî¬†superwhisper is hands-down the best dictation tool for Mac owners (sorry, Apple, native text-to-speech doesn't come close), and as Neil outlined during our conversation, making this fundamental switch will not only make you more productive, but also help you communicate more clearly‚Äîand even empathetically.",
