    "id": "post-2023-11-15-7130596752121860096",
    "title": "Remember the Borg from Star Trek?\"\n\"\"\n\"They were an ever-expanding ...",
    "date": "2023-11-15",
    "content": "Remember the Borg from Star Trek?\"\n\"\nThey were an ever-expanding alien group of cybernetic organisms linked to a hive mind.\n\"\nFoundation models (like OpenAI's GPT-4) are a bit like the Borg.\n\"\nThey get better (and thus more valuable to individuals and corporations) as they ingest more, high-quality data ‚Äî¬†thus, AI labs and foundation model providers are highly incentivized to expand the scope of training datasets to include proprietary and instrumentally valuable know-how, beyond what's publicly available on the internet.\n\"\nThis presents a question of existential importance to business owners everywhere:\n\"\nIs your business currently set up to outpace the rate of expansion of a foundation model's footprint in information space?\n\"\nFor many businesses, the answer will turn out to be \"No.\n\"\nAnd their strategic edge, the proprietary know-how that's afforded them a nice position in the market and healthy margins, will disintegrate, gradually and then suddenly as, for example, one of their competitors takes advantage of a first-mover opportunity to sell their own internal knowledge base to OpenAI via their new Data Partnerships program, and every ChatGPT Plus user in the world will be afforded the ability to bring those capabilities that they'd delegated to a third-party expert service provider in-house.\n\"\nIn short, the value of your business, either directly via a data acquisition or indirectly via an industry peer, gets absorbed by the Borg.\n\"\nThe good news is that you can actually leverage foundation model capabilities to accelerate forward motion on the frontier.\n\"\nBy using AI to make it easy for your employees to delegate those tasks that they need to do, know how to do, but really don't want to do (think: clerical and administrative work), they get back time, attention, and energy that they can invest in strengthening customer relationships and exploring new ways to expand the scope and elevate the quality of your business's products & services.\n\"\nAt a certain point, you might even use AI (as an engine) + your own proprietary data (as rocket fuel) to reach \"escape velocity,\" creating and capturing unprecedented value faster than your information edge disappears over the GPT-X event horizon.\n\"\nSo ‚Äî¬†are you ready to hit the gas and focus on the frontier?\n\"\nTo start experimenting with ways to use AI to automate support tasks and augment your staff's capabilities?\n\"\nTo survive move beyond the long shadow of the Borg by strategically integrating AI into your business's core capabilities?\n\"\n\"Whether you like it or not ‚Äî¬†it's approaching, and fast!",
