    "id": "post-2023-11-06-7127420366091640832",
    "title": "The billion dollar question for companies using AI is, \"How do I cr...",
    "date": "2023-11-06",
    "content": "The billion dollar question for companies using AI is, \"How do I create a machine that continuously acquires high-quality data on the frontier, gaining depth in a particular direction that exceeds the rate of expansion of what's 'in sample' for foundation models?\"\n\"\nWe can assume that all information and knowledge is eventually commoditized AND that profit can be found in the space between data-generating contact with a new pocket of reality and that data entering the GPT-X pre-training set.\n\"\nThere are and will continue to be short-lived arbitrage opportunities to index and pre-package information that's already been digitized before it's turned into a commodity.\n\"\nWhat's more interesting is the problem of doing this in a way that's coherent and durable ‚Äî by finding real-world problems, capturing insights by solving them, and then reinvesting those insights into accelerating forward movement in that problem space.\n\"\n\"Ultimately, you gotta think like an architect, not a house flipper.",
