    "date": "2023-10-16",
    "content": "Many thanks to Nicole Afton for facilitating a thought-provoking session on leading organizations through change initiatives! It was great exchanging perspectives with her, Rod Lacey, and Matt Johnson.\"\n\"\nSome key takeaways for executives leading their organizations through periods of rapid change:\n\"\nüî¢ Instead of overwhelming employees with data, AI can act as a \"smart indexing tool\" to help leaders grasp what matters most.\n\"\nü§ù Rather than automating tasks people enjoy, AI should complement human skills and energies. The goal is to lift burdens, not compete.\n\"\n‚è±Ô∏è Organizations shouldn't wait for the mythical \"perfect moment\" to understand employee motivations. Assess constantly with confidential pulse surveys.\n\"\nüó∫Ô∏è To drive rapid change, identify \"pioneers\" who get a thrill from trailblazing vs trying to convince the skeptics.\n\"\n‚úçÔ∏è Leaders shouldn't just communicate the \"what\", but the \"why\" of change repeatedly. Help employees write their own chapter in the story.\n\"\nI hope viewers left feeling optimistic about leading change when combining emerging technologies like AI with human-centric leadership.\n\"\nKudos again to Nicole for assembling a diverse panel to explore this complex topic.\n\"\n\"Please reach out if you would like to continue the discussion!",
