    "date": "2023-10-06",
    "content": "Feel free to ask me clarifying questions until you have enough information to proceed.\n\"\nAI pro tip: append this to your prompts for higher-quality results.\n\"\nEveryone is excited about forthcoming \"agentic\" AI capabilities, whereby ChatGPT et al will proactively retrieve and transform information on your behalf before producing an answer (√† la Code Interpreter/Advanced Data Analysis or the recently revived Web Browsing); however...\n\"\nRetrieval Augmented Generation works regardless of whether it‚Äôs the computer or the user who‚Äôs actually retrieving the information.\n\"\nIn my experience, it‚Äôs generally easier for the human to do it (especially if it's coming from your private repository), and probably will be for the foreseeable future.\n\"\n\"About a year ago, it occurred to me that \"the search engines of the future would ask YOU questions,\" and it's turned out to be the case with ChatGPT (and Claude) that as soon as you invite AI to become your curious thought partner‚Äînot just your eager first-year analyst to whom you delegate rote tasks‚Äîthat's when things start getting REALLY interesting.",
