    "title": "‚ôüÔ∏è \"Imagine a chessboard that extends across your entire enterprise",
    "date": "2023-09-24",
    "content": "‚ôüÔ∏è \"Imagine a chessboard that extends across your entire enterprise. AI helps you see moves you never even knew existed.\"\n\"\nI recently spoke with Jean Marc Goguikian, CEO at Konko.ai.\n\"\nOur conversation wasn't just about task automation. It was also about AI's potential to help us make better decisions under conditions of extreme uncertainty and complexity, thanks to broad-ranging simulations with \"synthetic humans.\n\"\nWhile, yes, AI models trained on your data will be able to draft your emails, they‚Äôll also be able to run high-dimensional multi-agent simulations, offering you a wide range of scenarios and analyses for critical business decisions (eg., preparing to have a tough conversation with a client or colleague).\n\"\nWe also discussed what he's learned from enterprise buyers about the remaining barriers to enterprise integration: data security and change management are still significant hurdles, but they are not insurmountable. \n\"\nOf similar importance is the ubiquitous need for thoughtful partnerships between AI providers and businesses (from SMBs to enterprises) interested in using the technology to catalyze their strategic initiatives and solve real problems (not just razzle dazzle with shiny tech).\n\"\nSo, what's next? Where should we expect to see the next great companies come into being as the next generation of AI technology comes online?\n\"\nJean-Marc emphasized the opportunity that lies in making AI accessible to the early majority, not just the innovators. The next s-curve of AI innovation is likely not about the creation of more complex toolsets; it'll be about crafting user-friendly yet powerful solutions that leverage the technology in nigh-invisible ways.\n\"\n\"üîó Want more insight? Reach out to Jean Marc Goguikian for a personalized touch and guidance on enterprise AI implementation.",
