    "content": "I often get asked how I concretely use AI as a thought partner, which is one of my favorite use cases to actually get more work done and elevate the quality of my ideas.\"\n\"\nThe obvious and immediate way to use AI is for drafting content. While that‚Äôs a great use case, you can actually engage with the technology more discursively. This helps improve the quality of what you post, share, or send by augmenting the robustness of your ideas with technology-assisted critical reasoning and reflection.\n\"\nI just recorded a short video showing you exactly how I do this in practice. I literally did this this morning just on my phone, and I‚Äôm going to include a link to the chat if you‚Äôd like to see the entire chat in full.\n\"\nAnyway, I know a lot of my posts are sort of abstract, so I thought I would make this as concrete as possible. I want to share a little bit more insight in regards to how I use AI on a day-to-day basis, especially AI as a thought partner.\n\"\nHope this helps!\n\"\n\"https://lnkd.in/eD3Zdfyc",
