    "id": "post-2023-09-11-7107073397527834624",
    "title": "üí™ Getting 10x Gains from AI: The Power of Ambitious Goals and Extr...",
    "date": "2023-09-11",
    "content": "üí™ Getting 10x Gains from AI: The Power of Ambitious Goals and Extreme Constraints ü§ñ\"\n\"\nI recently had an insightful conversation with Don Campbell about how to get more than just incremental improvements from AI.\n\"\nWe explored an approach I've found highly effective: pairing extremely ambitious goals with tight constraints on time and resources.\n\"\nCounterintuitively, this forces the type of radical rethinking that enables you to leapfrog vs incrementally progress.\n\"\nLet me explain...\n\"\nI first tried this approach at the beginning of the year, when a client reached out with an urgent request for AI assistance on a substantial deliverable for one of their clients with a fast-approaching deadline.\n\"\nI gave myself just 2 hours to build a data transformation script in Python for a client the output of which would normally have taken a human expert an entire day to complete.\n\"\nI promised the client a particular, quantifiable result by COB with a money-back guarantee. By relentlessly leveraging AI and coding tools like GPT-4 and GitHub Copilot, I delivered the desired outcome faster than either of us frankly thought would have been possible (and definitely wouldn't have been without AI).\n\"\nEven more powerful has been using this approach to create \"artisanal software\" for another client.\n\"\nEach week, I work live with a master operator at the company I'm serving to discover a problem in their workflow, design and build a solution, and ship it to production on the very same day.\n\"\nWe recently achieved this entire end-to-end innovation cycle in less than 60 minutes - discovering, designing, developing and deploying a completely customized web application feature, a process that in my decade of product experience would have taken weeks and a cross-functional team even just a few months ago.\n\"\nWhy does this work?\n\"\nAmbitious goals force you to deeply examine what would need to be true to achieve them. Extreme constraints leave no choice but to try creative new techniques. The combination drives breakthrough re-architectures.\n\"\nThe key is maintaining a \"hypergrowth mindset\" - lofty goals to push your limits, plus humility to learn from AI, even in areas where you're an expert. While you're in the zone, look for 10x contributions aligned to business objectives; delegate rote tasks to machines.\n\"\nThis compounding approach has transformed how I innovate with AI. I believe it can unlock new levels of transformational value for any leader or organization.\n\"\nAs you explore the potential of AI, try setting more ambitious targets under tighter constraints.\n\"\nThe breakthroughs may surprise you!\n\"\nI'd love to hear your thoughts on this technique - please like/comment!\n\"\n\"And thanks to Don Campbell for the thought-provoking discussion.",
