    "date": "2023-08-21",
    "content": "‚ÄúYou've really opened my eyes to what's possible when you reduce the time-to-capability side of the equation‚Ä¶‚ÄäThat surprised me the most.‚Äù ‚Äî¬†Nikhil Shenoy, CEO of Colvin Run Networks, Inc.\"\n\"\nOver three months, I‚Äôve had the pleasure of serving the team at Colvin Run as they drive innovation in the defense sector with cutting-edge technology, including generative AI.\n\"\nArmed with the hands-on experience I‚Äôve had helping clients (and myself) become more efficient by delegating clerical tasks to AI since ChatGPT was launched late last year (and nearly a decade of prior product management experience), I had a strong hunch that we‚Äôd be able to move at unprecedented speed in building a v1 prototype.\n\"\nBut, even with that hunch, I didn‚Äôt realize just how fast a small agile team can move when they‚Äôre armed with AI tools that plug into the product development process itself.\n\"\nFrom transcription and analysis of discovery interviews to GPT-4 (and Code Interpreter especially!) for translating plain English into boilerplate code to improving & refactoring that code with GitHub Copilot, all of those little productivity boosts add up‚Äîand we were able to create a tangible application, ready for real-world contact, in just a few hours.\n\"\nIf there‚Äôs one thing I hope other executives might take away from our experience, it‚Äôs this: When it comes to setting the bar in re a your AI initiative, RAISE YOUR EXPECTATIONS!\n\"\nInnovators can bootstrap software prototypes into existence and iterate faster than ever‚Äîit is even now possible to make and deploy live code changes in response to live end-user feedback.\n\"\nThis means that you should expect value from AI initiatives on day 1.\n\"\nWe are truly at the beginning of an innovation explosion: Custom software/information technology development capabilities that were only available to major corporations and equity-financed tech companies over the past few decades are now feasible for SMBs (and even sole proprietors) who want to move forward on the frontier and scale their operations with bespoke software that helps make operators more productive and gives executives their invaluable time back.\n\"\nAre you ready to start integrating AI into your business?\n\"\n\"Add your thoughts in a comment below!",
