    "date": "2023-07-31",
    "content": "New research out of The Wharton School supports my hunch a few months back about the positive role AI can play in augmenting the creative process.\"\n\"\nChatGPT-4 can generate ideas much faster and cheaper than students, the ideas are on average of higher quality (as measured by purchase-intent surveys) and exhibit higher variance in quality. More important, the vast majority of the best ideas in the pooled sample are generated by ChatGPT and not by the students. Providing ChatGPT with a few examples of highly-rated ideas further increases its performance.\n\"\nNext time you hit a roadblock, consider working with GPT-4 as a thought partner.\n\"\nAsk it to generate 20 out-of-the-box ideas for how you might overcome it.\n\"\nAll it takes is one good one to keep things moving forward.\n\"\n\"Full paper: https://lnkd.in/eV_Yw6J8",
