    "date": "2023-07-21",
    "content": "I've written previously about using AI as a \"thought partner,\" so today I thought I'd share a concrete example.\"\n\"\nI've been thinking a lot about interesting parallels between advances in machine learning and observations about human cognition made by classical thinkers like Plato, so decided to explore these ideas on my morning walk.\n\"\nI briefly chatted with ChatGPT (4) and asked for some help thinking things through.\n\"\nThe following is a summary of our discussion in the \"Axios Smart Brevity\" format (h/t to Leif Ulstrup for sharing this w me); I've included a link to the full conversation at the bottom:\n\"\nHeadline: Expanding Plato‚Äôs Pyramid: Navigating AI and Human Cognitive Evolution\n\"\nWhy It Matters: The ongoing evolution of artificial intelligence (AI) offers a mirror to human cognitive development, suggesting intriguing parallels and possible future intersections.\n\"\nNut Graph: Just as humans have ascended Plato‚Äôs Pyramid of Thought from sensory perception to abstract contemplation, AI is moving from deterministic, rule-based systems to probabilistic, learning-based models. The contrast and potential harmony between these trajectories could redefine our relationship with AI, altering how we think, work, and create.\n\"\nDetails: AI is descending Plato‚Äôs Pyramid, becoming more probabilistic and adaptive, resembling early stages of human cognition. This trend points to a future where AI handles tasks traditionally requiring human-like flexibility, freeing us for more complex cognitive endeavors.\n\"\nRelevance: For businesses and individuals, this progression suggests AI could become an even more integral part of our cognitive processes. AI tools could aid in making sense of complex systems, facilitating decision-making, and fueling creativity. The challenge lies in ensuring alignment with human values and maintaining transparency in AI decision-making.\n\"\nRelevant Quote: ‚ÄúLooking forward, it‚Äôs possible we might see the progression of both humans and AI toward a point of integration, where AI evolves to complement and augment human intelligence across the spectrum of cognitive tasks.‚Äù ‚Äì ChatGPT\n\"\nCritical Thinking Question: If we extend Plato‚Äôs Pyramid of Thought beyond the traditional four levels, into a future of integrated human and AI cognition, what ethical, societal, and technological challenges might we face, and how can we prepare for them?\n\"\n\"https://lnkd.in/eFmcyu_s",
