    "id": "post-2023-06-26-7079107513865924608",
    "title": "We're all Kardashians now",
    "date": "2023-06-26",
    "content": "We're all Kardashians now.\"\n\"\n(Or, thanks to AI, we will be, soon.)\n\"\nThe future of content marketing isn't SEO-optimized blogspam...it's \"hyper-reality.\n\"\nText chat (√† la ChatGPT) isn't the only way to interact with generative AI. In fact, it's probably the least interesting way to use the technology.\n\"\nThanks to tools like ElevenLabs, Midjourney, Kaiber, Runway's GEN-2, D-ID, Meta's MusicML, the cost of multimedia post-production is dropping like a rock.\n\"\nThat means you can take any idea and weave it into an attention-grabbing content nugget, perfectly tailored to fit the constraints of your public channel of choice (LinkedIn in my case).\n\"\nWhat does that mean for the future of content marketing (and marketing in general)?\n\"\nWell, when charisma is commoditized, the the differentiator that matters will be the core information‚Äîand, to anyone who has a love/hate relationship with digital media, this is a GOOD thing.\n\"\nYou won't have to hire an expensive agency to start publishing content. All you have to do is \"mine reality\" by tapping into the pool of digitized raw material that, thanks to remote work and the near-zero cost of digitization, all knowledge workers will be accumulating in the years ahead: Zoom recordings, interactions with clients, monologues prompted by context-aware AI like Rewind AI that elicits your expertise and helps you reflect on what you've learned over a given week with a short list of pointed questions.\n\"\nCredible experts have the most to gain: Information that's objectively interesting, novel, unique, and instrumentally valuable can be wrapped with AI-generated multimedia and frequently published, creating a trail of digital attractors that invite the right kind of attention and demonstrate trustworthiness.\n\"\nAI is already making it easy for individuals to gain HUGE leverage with AI-assisted coding. Software is a technology that turns labor into capital, and dropping development costs make artisanal software a reality for sole proprietors and small businesses that wouldn't have been able to afford tech teams even a year ago.\n\"\nSoon, AI will have the same effect on marketing. You won't need to pay the media piper to bootstrap distribution ex nihilo. All you need to do is create objective value and digitize the result, the process, and your clients' satisfaction.\n\"\nWith that raw material, your AI post-production assistant can do 90% of the post-production and ask for occasional editorial input. By untethering message and medium (vs. the traditional reality show setup), you get the best of both worlds: the benefits of a public profile without the risk that comes with publishing EVERYTHING (remember, you ultimately control what info gets indexed).\n\"\nWhat does that mean practically?\n\"\nIt's simple: Do good work, be curious, and remember to hit record.\n\"\n\"#ai #marketing #artificialintelligence",
