    "title": "ü´¢ Will AI decimate middle management?\"\n\"\"\n\"While, yes, many manage...",
    "date": "2023-06-19",
    "content": "ü´¢ Will AI decimate middle management?\"\n\"\nWhile, yes, many managers will need to retool or transition...skilled middle managers may actually benefit THE MOST from AI.\n\"\nUsing AI effectively requires you to orchestrate a system of diverse agents and continuously attend to individual components so that they work together in harmony.\n\"\nYou can think of AI pipelines (or \"tools\" or \"assistants\") as little machine processes, flexible cybernetic loops that you spin up into existence, not dissimilar to how a skilled player manages armies and specialized units in top-down strategy video games like Civilization and Starcraft.\n\"\nAgents periodically kick up exceptions to the player (or manager), and that person will need to address them on-the-fly + make appropriate adjustments (e.g., \"coaching,\" re-engineering system prompts) per feedback from a highly dynamic environment and the context of a higher-order goal.\n\"\nWe're left with a paradox.\n\"\nAs AI makes its way into all of our professional workflows, some big corporations may lay off middle managers, AND excellent middle managers who have spent their careers honing their management skills will have the most to benefit from AI.\n\"\n\"#artificialintelligence #management #digitaltransformation",
