    "content": "I just had the privilege of speaking with Liberia‚Äôs Vice President Jewel Taylor about the role of artificial intelligence as a force for progress and development in the country.\"\n\"\nIn the hands of curious, driven, and internet-connected young Liberians, technologies like OpenAI‚Äôs ChatGPT will catalyze greater participation in the global economy, enable unmediated capital flows into local economies (thanks to complementary platforms like Replit), and even serve as a critical tool in addressing public health needs‚Äîmental health especially‚Äîby making services more accessible and affordable, even in remote areas.\n\"\nToday, I‚Äôll be conducting a 2-hour AI workshop at a local high school in the nation‚Äôs capital, Monrovia, helping students get hands-on with the tools, start solving their most pressing problems, and imagine how they might leverage AI to build a better future for themselves and their communities.\n\"\n\"This will be my very first in-person AI group workshop, and I couldn‚Äôt be more enthusiastic about doing it in Liberia.",
