    "date": "2023-05-23",
    "content": "üî• Stuck in status update hell?! üî•\"\n\"\nLet's get you out...\n\"\nLast week, Vidya Santhanam and Fitbots OKRs invited me to present to business leaders & OKR practitioners around the world about how to conduct OKR status update meetings (that don't suck!)\n\"\nWe've probably all experienced that particularly unpleasant combination of dread, anxiety, and boredom that emerges before and during everyone's least favorite recurring \"check-in\" meeting.\n\"\nBUT ‚Äî¬†it doesn't have to be that way.\n\"\nIn fact, these meetings can even be fun & exciting.\n\"\nHow?\n\"\nTake a page from the TV production playbook by designing your weekly OKR sync meetings to be the perfect balance of familiar (a consistent, disciplined ritual with low reporting overhead) and novel (\"What's happening on this week's episode? I have to know how last week's cliffhanger gets resolved!\").\n\"\n\"Check out the whole presentation to learn some simple mechanics you can use to exit status update hell, enter weekly OKR sync paradise, and make these meetings a whole lot more interesting.",
