    "content": "AI tip of the day‚Ä¶\"\n\"\n‚ÄúStop typing!‚Äù\n\"\nIt‚Äôs one of the first behavior changes I recommend to clients I work with during our AI workshops.\n\"\nBut, what does typing have to do with using AI?\n\"\nWell, When it comes to using large language models like ChatGPT or GPT-4, you get what you give (aka ‚Äúgarbage in, garbage out‚Äù OR ‚Äúgold in, gold out‚Äù).\n\"\nIt‚Äôs not uncommon for first time ChatGPT users to walk away slightly amused but ultimately disappointed after entering a few queries like they would into Google.\n\"\nThey get results that are generic or bland, just like their short, simple queries.\n\"\nIt‚Äôs important to understand that the way you used traditional search engines is not how you should use large language models.\n\"\nIn fact, the more specific and precise you can get with your initial query and subsequent contributions to the ongoing conversation, the more value you will get out of the interaction.\n\"\nThis is not unlike delegating a task to or managing a smart and eager-to-please first year analyst. You want to give them as much context as you can about the problem space they will be operating in as well as your acceptance criteria, and how the particular task connects to a higher order objective.\n\"\nThinking deeply and strategically about what you want and why becomes more valuable and important.\n\"\nBut then you suddenly encounter a bottleneck: encoding all of that information into your query via natural language.\n\"\nThe average person speaks 2 to 3 times as many words per minute as the fastest typists can type.\n\"\nThe extra context and precision that is communicated in those additional words is highly correlated with the quality of the response and subsequent interactions that you have with the large language model.\n\"\nI‚Äôve switched almost completely to using text to speech dictation and automatic transcriptions of monologues and conversations across all of my devices.\n\"\nIt‚Äôs been a game-changer: I‚Äôm able to use AI more effectively, be more productive, give more attention to the task at hand or person I‚Äôm working with, and free up cognitive cycles from the drudgery of pressing keys.\n\"\nIf there‚Äôs one thing you do before opening up ChatGPT, it‚Äôs turning on dictation on your MacBook, Windows, PC, or smartphone, and using that as a method of input, rather than typing out short queries.\n\"\n(And don‚Äôt worry about mistakes - LLMs are surprisingly good at error correction. The transcript doesn‚Äôt need to be perfect. And it takes a lot less time to get the first draft out via dictation and then edit by hand than type it all out perfectly.)\n\"\n\"You‚Äôll be shocked by how much more value you get out of AI once you stop typing and start speaking naturally!",
