    "date": "2023-04-03",
    "content": "Are you interested in learning how to use AI, but aren't sure where to start?\"\n\"\nHere's how I've been using artificial intelligence‚Äîalmost daily since last fall!‚Äîto boost my efficiency, effectiveness, and provide more value to clients:\n\"\nüëÇ Better Listening in Meetings: By recording meetings and creating transcripts using Google Meet, I can focus more on what's being said and recall crucial details in follow-up communication. For example, before sending a check-in email to prospects, I revisit the transcript, find one or two items they were interested in but we didn't dig into, and then do a little research into the topic, including a valuable insight that recalls our discussion and provides some free value.\n\"\n‚úçÔ∏è Creating Higher-Quality Content, 10x FASTER: I use Vienna Hypertext's Scribe app to record monologues during my morning weekday walks and automatically transcribe them. Then, I shape the raw material with the help of OpenAI's GPT-4, Grammarly for copy edits, and Midjourney to create an eye-catching image for engaging text posts (including this one). More recently, I've been experimenting with D-ID and ElevenLabs for AI-generated audio and video.\n\"\nüö∂‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Getting More Active: Incorporating AI into my workflow has allowed me to work on-the-go (literally dictating to my phone, rather than typing on a laptop), resulting +10,000 steps per day. I use iOS speech-to-text to \"write\" and \"read\" material with Speechify.\n\"\nüëÅÔ∏è Consuming Content Efficiently: I use summarize.tech for YouTube videos and Snipd for podcasts to save time and focus on the most relevant information. This has helped me mine insights from long-form content and be more discerning in where I put my attention.\n\"\nüë®‚Äçüíª Building Functional Software: ChatGPT Plus helps me write and debug Python code for my projects, while Replit offers a marketplace for developers when I need extra help.\n\"\nüí¨ Providing Rapid and Precise Feedback/Instruction to Colleagues: I use Descript to record feedback and instructions (e.g. pitch deck first reads, where I verbalize my thoughts), then compress the transcript using ChatGPT Plus into TL;DRs that I send with the video. This has improved communication and saved a TON of time (say, vs. traditional written summaries via email or Docs).\n\"\nüó∫Ô∏è Exploring New Frontiers of Knowledge: AI helps me dive deep into topics relevant to my clients, identify top researchers, and even simulate panel discussions to understand different perspectives.\n\"\nIt's essential to note that AI is not perfect, and you should always double-check AI-generated outputs before sharing them with clients or team members.\n\"\nBut, once you start using AI to free up attention and energy to invest into building relationships, uncovering insights, cultivating a unique perspective, and spending more time in reality (unchained from your desk!), you'll never want to go back.\n\"\nOf the use cases above, is there one you'd like me to create a tutorial for? LMK in the comments!\n\"\n\"#ai #artificialintelligence",
