    "content": "My reading is that young (ie digital native) knowledge workers entering the global workforce from emerging markets have the most to gain.\"\n\"\nI expect that in not too long, an eager 19-yo in the Philippines or Tanzania armed with ChatGPT Plus, a Replit account, an internet-connected Android phone, and no student debt is going to be able to create more objective value (and at an incredibly low cost) than the average Ivy Masters alum in 2003.\n\"\nI‚Äôd bet we see IT productivity gains finally show up in the aggregate economic/productivity statistics in ‚Äò23/‚Äò24‚Äîand in a big way.\n\"\nWe live in interesting times!\n\"\nThere‚Äôs never been a better time to lean into digital transformation, get hands on with the tech, and start thinking about how you can use AI + an increasingly liquid global talent pool to gain leverage in your business.\n\"\n\" #ai #productivity #digitaltransformation",
