    "id": "post-2023-03-20-7043635428070936576",
    "title": "To understand AI, metaphors can be useful: as a tool that fits in y...",
    "date": "2023-03-20",
    "content": "To understand AI, metaphors can be useful: as a tool that fits in your hand, an eager-to-please first-year analyst, etc, BUT...\"\n\"\nI would argue that AI should be understood, first and foremost, as specifically ùò¢ ùò±ùò¶ùò≥ùò¥ùò∞ùòØùò¢ùò≠ ùò∑ùò¶ùò©ùò™ùò§ùò≠ùò¶ ùòßùò∞ùò≥ ùòØùò¢ùò∑ùò™ùò®ùò¢ùòµùò™ùòØùò® ùò§ùò∫ùò£ùò¶ùò≥ùò¥ùò±ùò¢ùò§ùò¶ (AKA digitized latent space, which continues to expand at an accelerating rate).\n\"\nThis will be an incredible boon for innovators and entrepreneurs who aren't afraid to travel to disparate pockets of the metaverse.\n\"\nHere's what I mean:\n\"\nAI is not a creative tool on its own, but it can catalyze human creativity by allowing individuals to traverse the vast surface area of digitized information and extract insights that are tailored to their goals. This is particularly useful given the increasing low-cost digitization of information, which has created a mind-boggling amount of data that can be accessed through our networks and computing architecture. However, the problem of search has been monopolized by companies like Google, which limits the ability of individual entrepreneurs to access and mine this information set.\n\"\nAI offers a solution to this problem by allowing individuals to perform personalized search functions using large language models, such as OpenAI's GPT algorithms (which helped me turn a voice memo into this post) or Facebook's recently released open-source models. This enables individuals to create their own search engines and traverse the latent space of data quickly and efficiently, extracting insights from voluminous, high fidelity primary sources‚Äîthen tailor those insights to their immediate needs and context. This unlocks creativity by providing raw material to turbocharge the creative process, allowing individuals to combine insights from disparate sources and solve proximal problems that stand in the way of longer-term goals.\n\"\nFurthermore, AI helps to deal with the problem of overspecialization by translating insights from deep areas of specialization (e.g., those locked up in academic journals and covered in a layer of jargon) into plain English and taking into account the context of the problem being solved. This enables individuals to generate a wide variety of hypotheses and engage in hyper-creative hypothesis generation based on their personal interests and strengths. AI ùó±ùóºùó≤ùòÄ ùóªùóºùòÅ ùòÄùóºùóπùòÉùó≤ ùóΩùóøùóºùóØùóπùó≤ùó∫ùòÄ ùóºùóª ùó∂ùòÅùòÄ ùóºùòÑùóª, but it allows individuals to scope and then conduct low-cost experiments to test their hypotheses and develop solutions with economic value.\n\"\nIt's important to note that AI will not generate value automatically, BUT it can catalyze human creativity by allowing individuals to traverse the expanding surface area of digitized information, then extract, translate, and combine insights. This unlocks the potential for creativity and innovation, enabling individuals to solve problems and develop solutions with economic value.\n\"\n\"Ready to dive in? Suit up and start exploring cyberspace w/ LLMs!",
