    "id": "post-2023-03-11-7040327116562845696",
    "title": "On the eve of widespread access to multimedia generative, AI (GPT-4...",
    "date": "2023-03-11",
    "content": "On the eve of widespread access to multimedia generative, AI (GPT-4 is allegedly launching next week), it‚Äôs more important than ever that we consider using blockchain infrastructure to stay tethered to reality.\"\n\"\nThe use of blockchain technology for transparency in supply chains gets a lot of attention. Many focus on its application in physical goods to ensure ethical production and sourcing. However, I believe the initial use case for blockchain technology lies in analyzing the information supply chain. By ‚Äúfollowing the money‚Äù (and in the case of cyberspace, reputation and attention invested) nearly instantly, we can understand who's funding the production of a particular bit of digital media and update our interpretation of said media accordingly.\n\"\nPublic blockchain technology can help quickly analyze the provenance and source of a particular piece of information, as well as understand the goals of the different entities that contributed to its production, dissemination, and amplification. This critical infrastructure can aid Americans in making better decisions and differentiating between useful information and disinformation or misinformation.\n\"\nI cannot tell you how many times I‚Äôve seen a tweet with a lot of engagement that is blatant propaganda, and then spent a few minutes digging only to find out that the source is someone affiliated with an obscure organization that, below the opaque surface, has obvious political goals and ‚Äúinteresting‚Äù board membership (eg via IRS filings on a non profit site).\n\"\nWe need to make it easier for Americans to discern information from disinformation, misinformation, and malinformation.\n\"\nIn my opinion, this is a promising use case for blockchain technology that the United States government should encourage and even invest in directly. Let us leverage this technology to ensure transparency in the information realm and empower individuals to make informed decisions in the 21st century.\n\"\n\"#blockchain #informationtransparency #criticalinfrastructure #publicsector #innovation",
