    "content": "Entering a new market is like crossing a foggy river...\"\n\"\n...and OKRs are the steppingstones that help you make it to a better future on the other side.\n\"\nYesterday, I had the opportunity to share a simple approach to objectives and key results with members of the Ask a Chief of Staff community.\n\"\nI've been experimenting with it over the past 3 years‚Äîlargely inspired by Christina Wodtke's \"Radical Focus\" and the writings of Hamilton Helmer, Richard Rumelt, and Roger Martin.\n\"\nIf you're a chief of staff, early stage founder, or innovation unit leader, I hope you might find it useful as a tool that yields insights (and, hopefully, PMF!) fast: https://lnkd.in/dazMzFZT\n\"\n\"#innovation #okrs #chiefofstaff #strategy",
