    "date": "2023-02-15",
    "content": "üîÆ What the heck is \"ùóΩùóøùóºùó±ùòÇùó∞ùòÅ ùóæùòÇùó∂ùóªùòÅùó≤ùòÄùòÄùó≤ùóªùó∞ùó≤?!\" üîÆ\"\n\"\nIt's a powerful tool for startup founders who want highly engaged customers...\n\"\nMatt Zerker spent a whole 2 hours breaking the concept down for me, and I left his workshop feeling energized, ready to use what he taught me to take my own business to the next level.\n\"\nFirst, a definition üëá\n\"\nAccording to ChatGPT, ùò≤ùò∂ùò™ùòØùòµùò¶ùò¥ùò¥ùò¶ùòØùò§ùò¶ means \"ùòÅùóµùó≤ ùó∫ùóºùòÄùòÅ ùóΩùó≤ùóøùó≥ùó≤ùó∞ùòÅ ùóºùóø ùó≤ùòÄùòÄùó≤ùóªùòÅùó∂ùóÆùóπ ùó≤ùó∫ùóØùóºùó±ùó∂ùó∫ùó≤ùóªùòÅ ùóºùó≥ ùòÄùóºùó∫ùó≤ùòÅùóµùó∂ùóªùó¥...\n\"\nIn ancient Greek philosophy and science, it was believed that the world was made up of four elements: earth, air, fire, and water. These elements were seen as the building blocks of everything in existence. The fifth element, the 'quinta essentia,' was believed to be a rare and elusive substance that was present in the heavens and was thought to be the purest and most perfect form of matter.\n\"\nùó£ùóøùóºùó±ùòÇùó∞ùòÅ ùóæùòÇùó∂ùóªùòÅùó≤ùòÄùòÄùó≤ùóªùó∞ùó≤ is the core means by which an entrepreneur uses his or her product to lead the user to an ideal future.\n\"\n(Fun fact: ùò±ùò≥ùò∞ùò•ùò∂ùò§ùòµ is comes from the Latin roots ùò±ùò≥ùò∞- and ùò•ùò∂ùò§ùò¶ùò≥ùò¶, meaning \"lead forward\")\n\"\nHere's how it works:\n1. Upon first contact with a user, the product ùò∑ùò™ùòµùò¢ùò≠ùò™ùòªùò¶ùò¥ the user. In other words, it grabs his or her attention by presenting something novel yet familiar, exciting, or surprising.\n2. Then, it helps the user picture a concrete ùò•ùò¶ùò¥ùò™ùò≥ùò¶ùò• ùòßùò∂ùòµùò∂ùò≥ùò¶ ùò¥ùòµùò¢ùòµùò¶, one where upon having used the product, he or she will have satisfied that desire.\n3. Finally, the product ùò•ùò¶ùò≠ùò™ùò∑ùò¶ùò≥ùò¥ ùò™ùòØùò§ùò≥ùò¶ùòÆùò¶ùòØùòµùò¢ùò≠ ùò∑ùò¢ùò≠ùò∂ùò¶ toward that promised longer-term end‚Äîan invitation to continue using the product.\n\"\nNow, on one hand, this model makes me a little uneasy...it's been used by some tech companies to exploit human weaknesses‚Äîto take advantage of the \"7 deadly sins\" as one famous investor put it‚Äîand keep them stuck in dopaminergic loops that are highly vitalizing (initially), but ultimately unsatisfying.\n\"\nBUT, on the other hand, the same mechanics can be used by entrepreneurs who want to use technology to help customers achieve long-term, deeply satisfying goals. üôè\n\"\nJust imagine...you're an entrepreneur who wants to do well by doing good, and you've built a durable, profitable business by doing the right thing & helping your customers flourish...\n\"\nYou can take your very first step by asking your most engaged user (or dream prospect) the following question:\n\"\nIf you could wave a magic wand and change ùò´ùò∂ùò¥ùòµ ùò∞ùòØùò¶ ùòµùò©ùò™ùòØùò®, what would it be?\" ü™Ñ\n\"\nYou might be surprised by what they say...\n\"\nThen, when you're ready, take the second step by sending Matt Zerker a DM with their answer, and he'll show you to discover your own product's quintessence and use it to deliver long-term, satisfying value to your customers.\n\"\nCan you remember the last magic moment you experience with a quintessential product?\n\"\n\"Share in the comments üí¨",
