    "title": "For the longest time, I struggled in my love/hate relationship with...",
    "date": "2023-02-13",
    "content": "For the longest time, I struggled in my love/hate relationship with tech...\"\n\"\nAs productive as I could be with my MacBook and iPhone, it was also all too easy to get distracted by all the shiny digital objects competing for my attention as I tried to get stuff done.\n\"\nAnd making the switch to remote work only made this worse.\n\"\nAs a resource-constrained startup founder, I realized that these distractions weren't just a nuisance; they were totally unacceptable.\n\"\nFinally, after years of experimentation, I figured out a robust solution.\n\"\nBy making a few simple changes on my phone and laptop, I've fundamentally transformed my relationship with my devices.\n\"\nInstead of seeing them as untrustworthy digital casinos‚Äîportals to attention-hungry digital monsters with insatiable appetites for human attention‚ÄîI now treat them as simple tools, trustworthy partners that act in service to my real-world goals.\n\"\nWhen I work with early-stage startup founders who also want to regain their attention and stay hyper-focused online, the very first thing I do is walk them through the same changes I made.\n\"\nI call it my \"slot machine-to-toaster\" checklist.\n\"\nBecause when you use your toaster, you want it to toast toast. You don't want to be bombarded with ads and algorithmically curated content that distracts you from enjoying breakfast.\n\"\nWhy should your expectations with your digital devices be any different?\n\"\nNow, I'm making that checklist available for just $0.99!\n\"\nReady to get your attention back and make it 10x easier to focus while getting more done than ever?\n\"\nGet it here: https://lnkd.in/eUpH6iMm\n\"\n\"#productivity #focus #remotework #attention",
