    "id": "post-2022-12-19-7010658471150764032",
    "title": "It's really dawning on me just how disruptive AI is going to be",
    "date": "2022-12-19",
    "content": "It's really dawning on me just how disruptive AI is going to be...\"\n\"\nThe primary interface through which we interact with machines and the digital world WILL NOT be screen-based or accessed through mouse-and-keyboard.\n\"\nIt will be via voice.\n\"\nGiven a sufficiently high-fidelity stream of information, AI agents will be able to retrieve and summarize pertinent data (e.g., context about your last conversation with a prospect + what they've been up to subsequently that you can use for a more effective second live meeting) via a natural language query.\n\"\nNo need to structure data into spreadsheets, CRMs, etc. before making it useful...\n\"\nMultibillion-dollar SaaS juggernauts with products that fit into a pre-AI world (e.g., w/ relational databases, point-and-click screen-based interfaces, specialized labor to maintain these dependencies) are going to struggle to compete with nimble upstarts that help users achieve the same goals with a new approach that is more effective and less costly, not just in terms of technical overhead, but‚Äîperhaps more importantly‚Äîless cognitively costly for users.\n\"\nWhat does this mean practically for you, today?\n\"\nRegardless of what your job is, there are two things you can do right now to start taking advantage of AI (yes, it's already valuable, and, yes, you're ready for it) and set yourself up for success as the technology continues to improve at an accelerating pace:\n\"\n1. Start recording EVERYTHING and grow your private information repository: Rewind AI and recorded conversations (with all parties' full consent, of course) via Google Meet or Zoom are great starting points. (When Apple's AR arrives, things will get really interesting...) I'd also recommend recording daily monologues about topics that are interesting to you, so you can mine them for valuable content (I did this last week to create a LinkedIn post...will share how I did later this week). This private knowledge repository WILL BE the source of your personal information edge, and thus, ability to grow wealth.\n\"\n2. Make time every day to practice using AI as a part of your workflow. OpenAI's ChatGPT is already ready. Ask it questions like it was a first-year analyst and give it knowledge work tasks at the same level (presentation outlines, email drafts, etc.). If you'd like to take things to the next level, try your hand at Midjourney or tune GPT to meet your more bespoke needs via the OpenAI Playground.\n\"\nUnfortunately, I think there are many knowledge workers and corporate leaders who will try to resist these changes (already artist communities are starting to declare Butlerian jihads against AI...), but if you can lean into the transformation as soon as possible, your future self will thank you for it.\n\"\nAre you ready to start wielding AI on a daily basis?!\n\"\nLike and reshare this post with a comment about how you might be able to use AI in your work today...\n\"\n\"#ai #digitaltransformation #technology #ar",
    "excerpt": "It's really dawning on me just how disruptive AI is going to be...\" \"\" \"The primary interface through which we interact with machines and the digital world...",
