    "id": "post-2022-12-15-7009184973379248128",
    "title": "As economists Ajay Agrawal, Joshua Gans, and Avi Goldfarb have note...",
    "date": "2022-12-15",
    "content": "As economists Ajay Agrawal, Joshua Gans, and Avi Goldfarb have noted in their bestselling book \"Power and Prediction: The Disruptive Economics of Artificial Intelligence,\" technology is most disruptive when it enables the creation of new systems (versus point solutions and applications).\"\n\"\nIn the book, they point out that while ultimately of marginal value in the context of existing systems, electricity proved transformational when it enabled entirely new systems of production (e.g., factories and machines, untethered from the energy source).\n\"\nSimilarly, I believe that AI, spatial computing, and public blockchain ledgers (all technologies that are currently of marginal value) will allow us to rebuild the corporation from first principles, untethering knowledge workers from space, time, and cultural context.\n\"\nThis new corporation will be glued together by a \"private AI,\" continuously fed streams of high-fidelity, proprietary information: meeting recordings and even real-time capture of knowledge work product creation via tools like Rewind AI. This will make it easier for information to be consumed and shared asynchronously, as employees' primary communication channel will be the corporate AI. Think: a Slack DM (or, more likely, a private Urbit group channel) you can ping at any point for the info you need to get your work done.\n\"\nThe cost of knowledge capture, management, and transfer goes essentially to zero, freeing up managers' time for more valuable (and largely relational) work, e.g., longer/more substantive 1:1s.\n\"\nThis new corporation will also tap into an unprecedentedly liquid global labor market. With on-chain reputation systems, we can verify that someone is credible while preserving their privacy, allowing us to transact with them on the blockchain.\n\"\nThis removes the need for costly and inefficient hiring processes that assume full-time employment. Hiring will happen incrementally and be project-based.\n\"\nReliable, real-time translation will lower linguistic barriers; cultural barriers are already coming down as the next generation of workers will have grown up largely on the internet, allowing them to access common contexts regardless of where they were born.\n\"\nFinally, spatial computing will allow us to convene remotely‚Äîprimarily for the purpose of generating emotional energy and building trust, NOT information sharing. We'll be fully liberated from our desks. Employees will be able to more easily build bonds via VR games like Rec Room, an activity that's far superior to Zoom happy hours...\n\"\nAI, VR/AR, and blockchain will allow us build new systems of coordinated human action‚Äîthe 21st-century corporation‚Äîfrom first principles, generate unprecedented wealth, and free up our invaluable attention for activities‚Äîliterally and figuratively‚Äîoutside of the office.\n\"\n#ai #technology #vr #blockchain #futureofwork\n\"\n\"https://lnkd.in/ecDxgJbY",
