    "date": "2022-12-05",
    "content": "I've often wondered if Google has been successful not due to their widespread use OKRs, but rather in spite of it...\"\n\"\nThat said, I love OKRs for keeping teams focused‚Äîbut only when there's a sound strategic foundation!\n\"\nOKRs\" (the tool + the process) are just a modern instantiation of timeless principles of human coordination toward a common end.\n\"\nIf you pick the wrong goal (or, IMO, more than one at a time), neither the tool nor the process can fix that.\n\"\n\"Another great Practitioner Insight from Roger Martin:",
