    "date": "2022-11-30",
    "content": "When it comes to personal productivity, we often think in terms of \"time management\" when we should instead be thinking in terms of \"energy management.\"\n\"\nWhile the number of hours in your day is fixed, your energy sources‚Äîyour physical, emotional, cognitive, and spiritual \"batteries\"‚Äîare not.\n\"\nWant to learn how to grow your daily reserves and start drawing from bigger batteries?\n\"\nThe first step is planning your day to account for energy oscillations, versus linear energy expenditures...\n\"\nIn other words, 90 minutes of work in the morning is NOT the same as 90 minutes of work in the afternoon!\n\"\n\"Learn more surprising insights (and practical techniques!) in this excellent visual summary of Jim Loehr, EdD and Tony Schwartz's \"The Power of Full Engagement\": https://lnkd.in/egwd26c5 #productivity #management #performance",
