    "id": "post-2022-11-29-7003420138049798145",
    "title": "\"Know thy time",
    "date": "2022-11-29",
    "content": "Know thy time.\" ‚Äî¬†Peter Drucker\n\"\nDrucker was a consultant, author, and innovator who, in the mid-20th century, pioneered many of the foundational techniques and concepts that make the modern corporation possible.\n\"\nAt the core of his approach were five imperatives for effective executives:\n\"\n1. Know thy time\n2. Focus on contribution\n3. Make strengths productive\n4. First things first\n5. Effective decisions\n\"\nTonight at 7pm ET, I'll speak with a panel of busy entrepreneurs about their approach to the first tenet.\n\"\nTime (and attention) management can be especially challenging in the age of digital distractions, making it more important than ever that founders, managers, and business leaders \"know thy time.\n\"\nNo matter what stage your business is at, how many employees you have, or where you sit on the team‚Äîyou ultimately only have about 100 hours of waking life per week (and ~16 hours of high-quality attention).\n\"\nLearn how to invest that time and attention into productive knowledge work with tips from founders and MIT Sloan School of Management alumni Adam J. Klein, Jared Ray Johnson, Vivian Graves Zeled√≥n, Jeffrey Tedmori, and‚Äîfingers crossed‚ÄîAdrian Cabrera de Luis, who'll be dialing in for a few minutes from around the globe.\n\"\n\"#management #entrepreneurship #productivity",
