    "title": "How much of your daily motivation comes from within? And how much f...",
    "date": "2022-11-09",
    "content": "How much of your daily motivation comes from within? And how much from without?\"\n\"\nHere‚Äôs a little thought experiment for you‚Ä¶\n\"\nIf you were to go without:\n- coffee\n- energy drinks\n- ADHD medication\n- nicotine (vaping, pouches, cigarettes)\n- video games\n- social media\n- access to electronic inboxes outside of a 1-hour period once per day, including email, Slack, Teams, and texting (and, yes, it‚Äôs feasible, even in the extreme‚Ä¶sci-fi author Neal Stephenson communicates by snail mail)\n- Netflix\n- YouTube\n- COLOR from all of your screen-based devices (I did this a year ago and have never regretted it)\n- fancy UIs from web pages (you can do this by turning on ‚Äúreader mode by default‚Äù in Safari), thereby collapsing the entire internet into images and text with a uniform typeface\n- more than one browser tab at a time\n- podcasts\n- unlimited music on Spotify\n- food prepared by someone other than yourself\n\"\nThen how difficult would it be to accomplish your daily workload?\n\"\nInstant access to the analog and digital drugs listed above makes it easy to slip into roles (and even entire professions) that are out of alignment with our sources of intrinsic motivation: a sense of purpose, derived from a long-term end that YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE TO BE GOOD AND TRUE and a steady stream of moment-by-moment challenges that you find joy in resolving AND for which you have a unique disposition to encounter with excellence and fortitude.\n\"\nUntil those two fundamental needs are met, it will always be difficult to wean yourself from the myriad 21st-century pick-me-ups, all of which come with a heavy dopaminergic debt burden.\n\"\nThe good news is that work can (and ultimately should IMO) be joyous.\n\"\nTo get to that point, start by opening your calendar and asking yourself a simple question: of all of the events to which I committed my attention last week, which did I find the most energizing?\n\"\nThen, WHY was it energizing?\n\"\nAnd finally, how can I get more of that in the week ahead (without external stimulation and outside of artificial simulations)?\n\"\nThe answers may surprise you‚Ä¶\n\"\n\" #work #motivation #dopamine",
