    "date": "2022-11-04",
    "content": "A wise man* once told me that a sign of maturity is when your present self consistently thanks your past self.\"\n\"\nWhen we plan for the future and resist temptation in the present, we are paradoxically better and better off in the present.\n\"\nThis is why it‚Äôs critical to front load your workday with the most cognitively taxing tasks on your plate.\n\"\nInstead of checking your email or catching up on Slack threads, consider creating an asset that will yield compounding value on its own: rohtinize a process to make it easier to delegate, create marketing content, or start testing your strategic assumptions with a rigorous financial model.\n\"\nBy investing your highest quality attention into the creation of ‚Äúcapital goods‚Äù for knowledge work, you shift your time preference towards the future.\n\"\nThe east stuff can wait ‚Äòtil the afternoon.\n\"\nAnd, next thing you know, you‚Äôll be thanking your past self every day!\n\"\n\"*Asbed Kassis",
