    "title": "No matter how much money you raise, there‚Äôs one constraint every fo...",
    "date": "2022-10-24",
    "content": "No matter how much money you raise, there‚Äôs one constraint every founder at every stage will have to deal with‚Ä¶\"\n\"\nIt‚Äôs your limited attention.\n\"\nThe truth is, you only have about 100 waking hours every week.\n\"\nAnd only about four ‚Äúhigh-quality‚Äù hours per day.\n\"\nAre you directing your attention toward the right problems?\n\"\nAttention is like money. You can spend it frivolously or use it to create wealth.\n\"\nAre you ‚Äúpaying‚Äù attention or are you investing it?\n\"\nRight now, go look at your iOS or Android screen time analytics and see where those 100 hours went last week‚Ä¶\n\"\nDid you create marketing assets? Document processes? Strengthen relationships? Build technology?\n\"\nOr did you give your hours to social media, YouTube, email, mobile games, Slack, and frivolous Zoom meetings?\n\"\nAnd what about your teammates? Have you built a culture and a work environment that values focus and outcomes? Is their clear alignment across the company on your long-term mission and vision + shorter-term strategic objective?\n\"\nOr do you tolerate distractions that eat away at employee attention (and ultimately your company‚Äôs checking account)?\n\"\nAs we exit the age of 0% interest rates, investors will expect profitability at earlier stages, and you‚Äôll need to compete with other hungry entrepreneurs for smaller pools of capital.\n\"\nThe founders who will come out ahead in the next decade are those who master attention management.\n\"\nBetween now and IPO, every hour counts.\n\"\nSo, how do you stay focused in the age of digital distractions?\n\"\n\"Share your tips in a comment below üëá",
