    "id": "post-2022-09-16-6976599753505566720",
    "title": "Ever worry that you're wasting your life on digital distractions?\"\n...",
    "date": "2022-09-16",
    "content": "Ever worry that you're wasting your life on digital distractions?\"\n\"\nFor almost my entire life, I was locked in a seemingly un-winnable struggle with my devices...often finding myself lost in a YouTube rabbit hole or state of social media hypnosis when I should have been making progress on my most important task.\n\"\nIt left me feeling empty and guilty. I wasn't getting as much done as I'd hoped, and strangely, every bout of distraction left me feeling exhausted, not recharged, even though I deluded myself into believing it was a form of relaxation.\n\"\nSo, one day, I decided to face reality by sitting down with an Excel spreadsheet and calculating precisely how much attention I had to spend (or, even better, invest) every day, week, month, year...and perhaps even the rest of my life.\n\"\nIt was a game-changer.\n\"\nNow I'm sharing what I've built with anyone who wants to regain control of their attention and start investing it into the things that actually matter.\n\"\nReady to liberate yourself from siren songs of digital media?\n\"\nTake a first step by building out your own attention budget‚Äîand confronting the inescapable reality of just how time and energy you have left to give.\n\"\n\"https://lnkd.in/eDqAqQ4g",
